wl gpro0wi8 q66pz984 b1v8xokw\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/hashtag\\/zenitteam?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZWeFGPBWjx2dseTQANpjrF2lCzdWphKZ3Qc0SAad851i2YVdatF6HOq6gvHI783GJPhw52MarjVMq9Fr5uKCTaXpmfSx2i4pw1z3l42vb6AsIpKhqxTvn6S6Yanp5tZtPsyQzGEtt4ORE_p7YfvN_Q6&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\\\" role=\\\"link\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" style=\\\"cursor: pointer; outline: none; list-style: none; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; text-align: inherit; display: inline; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; box-sizing: border-box; font-family: inherit;\\\"><font color=\\\"#000000\\\">#ZENITTeam<\\/font><\\/a><\\/span><\\/div><div dir=\\\"auto\\\" style=\\\"font-family: inherit;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\"><a class=\\\"oajrlxb2 g5ia77u1 qu0x051f esr5mh6w e9989ue4 r7d6kgcz rq0escxv nhd2j8a9 nc684nl6 p7hjln8o kvgmc6g5 cxmmr5t8 oygrvhab hcukyx3x jb3vyjys rz4wbd8a qt6c0cv9 a8nywdso i1ao9s8h esuyzwwr f1sip0of lzcic4wl gpro0wi8 q66pz984 b1v8xokw\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/hashtag\\/bestpartofdriving?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZWeFGPBWjx2dseTQANpjrF2lCzdWphKZ3Qc0SAad851i2YVdatF6HOq6gvHI783GJPhw52MarjVMq9Fr5uKCTaXpmfSx2i4pw1z3l42vb6AsIpKhqxTvn6S6Yanp5tZtPsyQzGEtt4ORE_p7YfvN_Q6&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\\\" role=\\\"link\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" style=\\\"cursor: pointer; outline: none; list-style: none; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; text-align: inherit; display: inline; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; box-sizing: border-box; font-family: inherit;\\\"><font color=\\\"#000000\\\">#bestpartofdriving<\\/font><\\/a><\\/span><\\/div><\\/div>\"}', '{\"en\":\"hybrid with gas installation LPG ZENIT\"}', '63711644664784.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'hybrid-and-gas-start-of-the-week', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(20, '{\"en\":\"Why study in Poland\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;\\\">You will enjoy a high quality of teaching but also have a chance to pursue your future career in EU. Polish schools compete with each other not only to provide a wide variety of high quality courses, but also offer attractive tuition fees in programs such as MBBS, engineering, international business, tourism, hospitality and other courses. POLAND (POLSKA) lies in the very heart of the European continent making it easy access to and from other popular European destinations.<\\/p><p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;\\\">Poland is an incredible country with a diverse and rich educational history. Studying in Poland will give you a European degree at a low cost. Polish schools compete with each other not only to provide a wide variety of high-quality courses but also offer attractive tuition fees in programs such as MBBS, engineering, international business, tourism, hospitality and other courses. POLAND (POLSKA) lies in the very heart of the European continent making it easy access to and from other popular European destinations. The majority of private higher educational institutions offer 3-year courses of study for a Bachelor\\u2019s degree. Only about twelve institutions offer a 5 year course of study which leads to a Master\\u2019s degree and only one has obtained the right to confer the doctorate degree. There are now 12 private institutions that occupy top positions relating to the standards of tertiary education that are published every year by many institutions. Private higher education institutions are decidedly more expensive for students than are the public. The public institutions are taking note and are taking measures to reduce these proportions. Nearly 100% of private institutions are funded from tuition fees and not from the state budget. They are dependent on their markets.<\\/p><p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;\\\">By 2010 Poland is hoping that the number of people enrolled in higher education should rise 35-40% and 40-45% in 2020. These increases will raise new challenges for higher education in regards to its accessibility, particularly for the inhabitants of villages and small towns. Ideally Poland wants to decrease the differences in the level of civilization between the country regions and the various social groups. With the spreading effects of the metropolises, the situating of universities and colleges in the medium-sized cities offers a chance to establish education centres of high quality and the possibility of creating innovative processes. Highly International Education.<\\/p><h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 15px; text-transform: capitalize;\\\">Poland Is A Member Of The European Union<\\/h3><p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;\\\">It joined the Schengen Area in 2007. As a result passport checks are abolished on Poland\\u2019s borders to Germany, Slovakia, Czech Republic and Lithuania. It practically means that persons admitted to the Schengen Area can travel hassle-free between 24 countries of the Schengen Area without internal land and sea border controls, from Portugal to Poland and from Greece to Finland.<\\/p><p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bolder;\\\">Polish institutions of higher education<\\/span>&nbsp;participate in international student exchange programmes and engage in bilateral agreements and individual exchange programmes pursued by particular schools. All these initiatives enhance the development of relations between Polish and foreign institutions of higher education. The number of Polish institutions of higher education awarded an Erasmus University Charter approach 200 and the mobility of Polish students grows rapidly.<\\/p><p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bolder;\\\">Poland\\u2019s education market has been the most dynamically developing<\\/span>&nbsp;one in Europe during the last twelve years. The number of higher education institutions has increased five fold while the number of students quadrupled. Each year almost half a million young people begin their education at universities and colleges.<\\/p><p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bolder;\\\">Polish academic traditions reach back to 14th century<\\/span>&nbsp;some of the Europe\\u2019s oldest universities can be found here. The Jagiellonian University of Cracow was established in 1364. Nicholas Copernicus and Marie Sk\\u0142odowska-Curie are among great names of Polish scientists known and admired worldwide.<\\/p><p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bolder;\\\">Polish universities offer high quality studies and are an integral part of the European education space<\\/span>.&nbsp;All leading universities offer programmes taught in English, these include medicine, engineering, humanities, business and finance. Poland takes active part in the Bologna Process. Thanks to the&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bolder;\\\">ECTS<\\/span>&nbsp;(European Credit Transfer System) students can be fully mobile, and continue education in other countries.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"You will enjoy high quality of teaching, but also have a chance to pursue your future career in EU. Polish schools compete with each other not only to provide a wide variety of high quality courses, but also offer attractive tuition fees in programs such as MBBS, engineering, international business, tourism, hospitality and other courses. POLAND (POLSKA) lies in the very heart of the European continent making it easy access to and from other popular European destinations.\"}', '75861644672157.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'why-study-in-poland', 1, NULL, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `excerpt`, `feature_img_name`, `feature_img_original_name`, `feature_img_mime`, `feature_img_ext`, `status`, `tags`, `read`, `headline`, `front_slider`, `highlight`, `publish_status`, `published_year`, `published_number`, `published_at`, `slug`, `addedby_id`, `writer_id`, `editedby_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(21, '{\"en\":\"Study in Japan | Education in Japan | Study Abroad in Japan\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h2 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-weight: 700; line-height: var(--component-heading-line-height,1.2); color: rgb(62, 103, 219); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-xxxs)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1));\\\">Study in Japan | Education in Japan | Study Abroad in Japan<\\/h2><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Study Abroad in Tokyo<\\/span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Study Abroad in Yokohama<\\/span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Study Abroad in Osaka<\\/span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Education in Tokyo&nbsp;<\\/span>|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Education in Yokohama&nbsp;<\\/span>|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Education in Osaka<\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">Japan is a land of contrasts, preserving old traditions connected to the ancient Japanese civilization, like the Buddhist heritage, and, at the same time, the nation leads in scientific research, mainly technology, famous for manufacturing robots. Every year over 100,000 foreign students from every corner of the globe&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">enroll in Japanese universities<\\/span>&nbsp;and colleges.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">With a total three million students enrolled at over 1,200 universities and junior colleges, Japan provides a wealth of opportunities for students wishing to pursue tertiary education. In Japan, higher educational institutions concentrate on academic success based on innovative and creative concepts, but also set great interest in the production of human welfare.<\\/p><h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-weight: 700; line-height: var(--component-heading-line-height,1.2); color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-xxxs)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1));\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\\">International students can choose to study between these five types of institutions of higher education:<\\/span><\\/h3><ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-size: 16px;\\\"><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Universities (undergraduate courses)<\\/span>: There are more than 700 universities in Japan, including national, public and private ones. The duration of study in an undergraduate university takes around 4 to 5 years.<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Graduate schools<\\/span>: Masters programme takes around 2 years<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Junior colleges<\\/span>: The duration of study is takes 2 to 3 years<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Special training colleges (post-secondary courses)-&nbsp;<\\/span>Such schools are positioned as higher educational institutions in Japan, providing vocational education<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Colleges of technology<\\/span>: five and a half years for merchant shipping courses. There are approximately 60 colleges of&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">technology in Japan<\\/span>.<\\/li><\\/ul><h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-weight: 700; line-height: var(--component-heading-line-height,1.2); color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-xxxs)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1));\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\\">Practical Information<\\/span><\\/h3><h4 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-weight: 700; line-height: var(--component-heading-line-height,1.2); color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-xxxs)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1));\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\\">How to apply to universities in Japan<\\/span><\\/h4><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">To apply directly, download the application form from the official website dedicated to higher education&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">studies in Japan<\\/span>. A separate application form should be filled and submitted by students who wish to apply at more than one university.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">If the university accepts the student based on their qualifications, the student will receive an offer letter. Students are supposed to respond to this letter by signing and sending an acceptance of offer back to the institution to confirm your offer.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; text-align: center;\\\">Top Education in Japan, with top admission in Japan in top courses in Japan in top bachelor courses in Japan, top master\\u2019s courses in Japan, top medical courses in Japan, top MBBS courses in Japan, top business courses in Japan, top MBA courses in Japan for top higher education in Japan and also for top study abroad in Japan to study in Japan.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Japan is a land of contrasts, preserving old traditions connected to the ancient Japanese civilization, like the Buddhist heritage, and, at the same time, the nation leads in scientific research, mainly technology, famous for manufacturing robots. Every year over 100,000 foreign students from every corner of the globe enroll in Japanese universities and colleges.\"}', '44061644672443.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'study-in-japan-education-in-japan-study-abroad-in-japan', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(22, '{\"en\":\"Study in Germany Education\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"line-height: 2.2rem; font-size: 16px; margin: 0.5rem 0px 1.5rem; text-align: justify; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Fira Sans\', \'Droid Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #000000;\\\">Is Germany your study destination? Have you plans to graduate or postgraduate at the best university in Germany? Do you require guidance in choosing the best university? We can help you! We have top education consultants with vast experience in assisting students with the best German university. Germany has the best universities that offer a wide range of courses. There are 400+ institutions that offer higher education in Germany. Germany is ranked among the world&rsquo;s top destinations for international students. In the latest database of the German Academic Exchange Service (DAAD), international students can choose from more than 1300 study programs based in English. Many courses have no tuition fee, which is advantageous for international students, so the cost of living is affordable. According to German law, international students are allowed to work part-time for 20 hours a week, and it is estimated that 60% of international students work part-time while they study.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 class=\\\"title-large\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 2rem; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0px; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; width: 1203.33px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Fira Sans\', \'Droid Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #000000;\\\">Germany- New Land of Opportunities<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 2.2rem; font-size: 16px; margin: 0.5rem 0px 1.5rem; text-align: justify; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Fira Sans\', \'Droid Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #000000;\\\">So why choose Sulekha for your study abroad education and career. The most popular education hubs in Germany that Indian students target are Berlin, Cologne, Dresden, Frankfurt, Hamburg, Heidelberg, and Munich. Sulekha has the best-verified education consultants offering and helping students with admissions consulting, choosing the top universities, and assisting students in choosing the suitable course that accompanies Germany\'s job opportunities. Our consultants also help in end-to-end services like application process, visa processing, financial and scholarship counseling, admission guidance, travel assistance, interview preparations, and other documentation. They stand as your guide in helping you in your academics and career goals.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"line-height: 2.2rem; font-size: 16px; margin: 0.5rem 0px 1.5rem; text-align: justify; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Fira Sans\', \'Droid Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #000000;\\\">Sulekha is the best online platform with verified top German education consultants, helping 500+ students achieve their academic and career goals. Register today at Sulekha and get assured admits to top universities in Germany.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Germany has the best universities that offer a wide range of courses.\"}', 'study-in-germany-education_941644672646.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'study-in-germany-education', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(23, '{\"en\":\"Study in China | Education in China | Study Abroad in China\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h2 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-weight: 700; line-height: var(--component-heading-line-height,1.2); color: rgb(62, 103, 219); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-xxxs)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1));\\\">Study in China | Education in China | Study Abroad in China<\\/h2><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Study Abroad in Shanghai<\\/span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Study Abroad in Beijing<\\/span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Study Abroad in Shenzhen<\\/span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Study Abroad in Guangzhou<\\/span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Study Abroad in Chengdu<\\/span>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Education in Shanghai&nbsp;<\\/span>|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Education in Beijing&nbsp;<\\/span>|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Education in Shenzhen&nbsp;<\\/span>|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Education in Guangzhou&nbsp;<\\/span>|&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">Education in Chengdu<\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">China has more than 2,000 higher education institutions all over the country, and some of Asia\\u2019s and the world\\u2019s top universities belong to China. While the country is considered to be the top country in which sends students to study abroad, it is also considered that the country attracts foreign students to come and study in the country<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">According to&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">China\\u2019s Ministry of Education<\\/span>, there were nearly 500,000 foreign students in the country in 2018 and this is rising year after year.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">Many&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">courses in China<\\/span>&nbsp;are taught in Mandarin instead of English so, if the student is planning on pursuing a course in Mandarin, the student should present a certificate of a passing grade in the Hanyu Shuiping Kaoshi (HSK) exam, between levels 3 to 8.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">There are various options available to foreign students looking to<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">&nbsp;study in China<\\/span>. Some of the most popular undergraduate and postgraduate courses are currently:<\\/p><ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-size: 16px;\\\"><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\">Computer Science<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\">General Engineering<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\">International Business<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\">Economics<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; line-height: var(--component-body-line-height);\\\">Languages<\\/li><\\/ul><h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-weight: 700; line-height: var(--component-heading-line-height,1.2); color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-xxxs)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1));\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\\">Practical Information<\\/span><\\/h3><h4 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; font-weight: 700; line-height: var(--component-heading-line-height,1.2); color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-xxxs)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1));\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\\">How to apply to universities in China<\\/span><\\/h4><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">To apply directly, download the application form from the official website dedicated to higher education&nbsp;<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;\\\">studies in China<\\/span>. A separate application form should be filled and submitted by students who wish to apply at more than one university.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">If the university accepts the student based on their qualifications, the student will receive an offer letter.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;;\\\">Students are supposed to respond to this letter by signing and sending an acceptance of offer back to the institution to confirm your offer.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: calc(var(--space-sm)*var(--text-vspace-multiplier, 1)); margin-left: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: var(--component-body-line-height); font-family: &quot;Roboto Condensed&quot;; text-align: center;\\\">Top Education in China, with top admission in China in top courses in China in top bachelor courses in China, top master\\u2019s courses in China, top medical courses in China, top MBBS courses in China, top business courses in China, top MBA courses in China for top higher education in China and also for top study abroad in China to study in China.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"China has more than 2,000 higher education institutions all over the country, and some of Asia\\u2019s and the world\\u2019s top universities belong to China.\"}', '59811644672791.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'study-in-china-education-in-china-study-abroad-in-china', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(24, '{\"en\":\"The best education consultants in Hong Kong\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h3 style=\\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-left: -1.5px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 2.2rem; color: #1c1c1c; letter-spacing: 1.5px; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\">1. Foundation Global Education<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">At Foundation, the goal is to find the best educational fit for your child. The team brings decades of experience to bear in placing your child in the right international school, boarding school, or university&mdash;and they even offer help for summer schools, too. If your child is planning a non-traditional route for university, Foundation can help, too&mdash;their Accelerating Athletes Program can help aspiring athletes get into an NCAA school in the US or perhaps rowing for Oxford at Henley, while their services for gifted\\/learning differences students offer support for students with special educational needs.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">The brand&rsquo;s full-service approach includes everything from campus visits and profile building to interview prep and essay training. For parents not familiar with the education systems in different countries, they also offer alternatives to traditional options&mdash;for example, introducing the American Liberal Arts colleges.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\"><em><a style=\\\"color: #e84625; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; transition: all 0.1s ease-in-out 0s; border: 0px; border-radius: 0px !important;\\\" title=\\\"\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/foundationge.com\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow noopener\\\" data-original-title=\\\"\\\">Foundation Global Education<\\/a>, 13\\/F Chinachem Hollywood Centre, 1 Hollywood Road, Central, Hong Kong, p. 3107 8810<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-left: -1.5px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 2.2rem; color: #1c1c1c; letter-spacing: 1.5px; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\">2. Capstone<\\/h3>\\r\\n<figure id=\\\"attachment_178820\\\" class=\\\"wp-caption aligncenter\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px auto 28px; max-width: 100%; clear: both; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; width: 900px;\\\" aria-describedby=\\\"caption-attachment-178820\\\"><img class=\\\"wp-image-178820 size-medium lazyloaded\\\" style=\\\"border: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 1000ms ease 0ms; min-width: 100%; margin: 0px auto;\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/capstone-900x643.jpg\\\" sizes=\\\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\\\" srcset=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/capstone-900x643.jpg 900w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/capstone-768x549.jpg 768w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/capstone.jpg 1400w\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"900\\\" height=\\\"643\\\" data-srcset=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/capstone-900x643.jpg 900w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/capstone-768x549.jpg 768w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/capstone.jpg 1400w\\\" data-src=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/capstone-900x643.jpg\\\" data-sizes=\\\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<figcaption id=\\\"caption-attachment-178820\\\" class=\\\"wp-caption-text\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 1.4rem; text-align: center; color: #2db3b1; padding: 5px 0px;\\\">(Photography: Capstone via Facebook)<\\/figcaption>\\r\\n<\\/figure>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">A leading education consultancy, Capstone has a brilliant track record for admissions, especially when it comes to US and UK boarding schools and universities. Capstone has placed students in highly sought-after boarding schools such as Philip Exeter, Hotchkiss, Deerfield, Eton, Harrow, and Winchester; university prospects have gained admission to Harvard, Yale, Stanford, Brown, Cornell, MIT, and&mdash;over the pond&mdash;Oxbridge, LSE, King&rsquo;s, St Andrews, and Edinburgh.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">In Hong Kong, top picks for previous students have included the Canadian International School, Chinese International School, German Swiss International School, and Island School. Capstone&rsquo;s comprehensive services provide a competitive advantage with personalised packages that range from advice and interview prep to essay and exam coaching.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\"><em><a style=\\\"color: #e84625; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 