-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\\\" \\/><\\/a><\\/div>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"right\\\" style=\\\"display: inline-block; vertical-align: middle; width: calc(100% - 300px); padding: 0px 30px;\\\"><a class=\\\"hc-category\\\" style=\\\"background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; transition: all 0.1s ease-in-out 0s; border: 0px; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: bambino-regular, sans-serif; font-size: 1.2rem; white-space: nowrap; text-overflow: ellipsis; overflow: hidden; width: 100%; letter-spacing: 3px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; color: #ffffff !important; border-radius: 0px !important;\\\" title=\\\"\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/thehoneycombers.com\\/hong-kong\\/hong-kong-with-kids\\/\\\" data-toggle=\\\"tooltip\\\" data-placement=\\\"top\\\" data-original-title=\\\"View more posts\\\">KIDS &amp; FAMILY<\\/a>\\r\\n<h3 class=\\\"title\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: -1.5px; font-size: 2.5rem; color: #1c1c1c; letter-spacing: 1.5px; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-family: keplerstd-disp, serif !important;\\\"><a class=\\\"mid_ad_link\\\" style=\\\"background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; transition: all 0.1s ease-in-out 0s; color: #ffffff !important; border-radius: 0px !important; border: 0px !important;\\\" title=\\\"\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/thehoneycombers.com\\/hong-kong\\/how-to-study-for-exams-guide-to-revision-strategies\\/\\\" data-toggle=\\\"tooltip\\\" data-placement=\\\"bottom\\\" data-original-title=\\\"Read related post\\\">11 tips exam prep from an expert educator<\\/a><\\/h3>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-left: -1.5px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 2.2rem; color: #1c1c1c; letter-spacing: 1.5px; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\">3. Arch Education<\\/h3>\\r\\n<figure id=\\\"attachment_178821\\\" class=\\\"wp-caption aligncenter\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px auto 28px; max-width: 100%; clear: both; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; width: 900px;\\\" aria-describedby=\\\"caption-attachment-178821\\\"><img class=\\\"size-medium wp-image-178821 lazyloaded\\\" style=\\\"border: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 1000ms ease 0ms; min-width: 100%; margin: 0px auto;\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/arch-900x643.jpg\\\" sizes=\\\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\\\" srcset=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/arch-900x643.jpg 900w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/arch-768x549.jpg 768w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/arch.jpg 1400w\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"900\\\" height=\\\"643\\\" data-srcset=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/arch-900x643.jpg 900w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/arch-768x549.jpg 768w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/arch.jpg 1400w\\\" data-src=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/arch-900x643.jpg\\\" data-sizes=\\\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<figcaption id=\\\"caption-attachment-178821\\\" class=\\\"wp-caption-text\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 1.4rem; text-align: center; color: #2db3b1; padding: 5px 0px;\\\">(Photography: ARCH Education via Facebook)<\\/figcaption>\\r\\n<\\/figure>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Whether it&rsquo;s skills-based enrichment courses, tuition, test prep, or admissions advice, Arch Education stands ready to help all students aged between seven and 18 years on their path to educational success. The heart of their offering is bespoke admissions guidance for boarding schools and universities in the UK and US&mdash;and boy, do they have a track record to back it up.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Arch boasts a 90% acceptance rate at Ivy League or top 50 US schools and over 180 offers from Oxbridge. In addition, Arch students have a 100% acceptance rate at boarding schools, and have achieved stellar results in exams&mdash;think 82% receiving over 40 points in the International Baccalaureate and 81% getting over 1450 on the SAT. Arch also offers useful specialized pre-university courses, including the University of London International Foundation Program and St George&rsquo;s University Pre-Medicine Foundation Program.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\"><em><a style=\\\"color: #e84625; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; transition: all 0.1s ease-in-out 0s; border: 0px; border-radius: 0px !important;\\\" title=\\\"\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.arch-education.com\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow noopener\\\" data-original-title=\\\"\\\">Arch Education<\\/a>, 2&amp;4\\/F Wilson House, 19-27 Wyndham Street, Central, Hong Kong, p. 8191 1388<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-left: -1.5px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 2.2rem; color: #1c1c1c; letter-spacing: 1.5px; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\">4. ITS Education<\\/h3>\\r\\n<figure id=\\\"attachment_178822\\\" class=\\\"wp-caption aligncenter\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px auto 28px; max-width: 100%; clear: both; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; width: 900px;\\\" aria-describedby=\\\"caption-attachment-178822\\\"><img class=\\\"size-medium wp-image-178822 lazyloaded\\\" style=\\\"border: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 1000ms ease 0ms; min-width: 100%; margin: 0px auto;\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/its-900x643.jpg\\\" sizes=\\\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\\\" srcset=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/its-900x643.jpg 900w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/its-768x549.jpg 768w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/its.jpg 1400w\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"900\\\" height=\\\"643\\\" data-srcset=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/its-900x643.jpg 900w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/its-768x549.jpg 768w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/its.jpg 1400w\\\" data-src=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/its-900x643.jpg\\\" data-sizes=\\\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<figcaption id=\\\"caption-attachment-178822\\\" class=\\\"wp-caption-text\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 1.4rem; text-align: center; color: #2db3b1; padding: 5px 0px;\\\">(Photography: ITS Education Asia via Facebook)<\\/figcaption>\\r\\n<\\/figure>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">ITS can help at every level of schooling and any unique circumstance. The team&mdash;which speaks, English, Cantonese, Mandarin, French, and Italian&mdash;has everything covered, from practising pre-school interviews and getting into top international schools to exam prep and crafting stellar university applications.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">In Hong Kong, they offer tuition for IB, IGCSE, A-Levels, and specialise in admissions to top-tier UK and US universities. Their no-nonsense&mdash;but tactful!&mdash;approach will ensure that your child is carefully guided on their quest to get the best education possible&mdash;and that includes recommendations on international boarding schools and special needs education options.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\"><em><a style=\\\"color: #e84625; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; transition: all 0.1s ease-in-out 0s; border: 0px; border-radius: 0px !important;\\\" title=\\\"\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.itseducation.asia\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow noopener\\\" data-original-title=\\\"\\\">ITS Education<\\/a>&nbsp;has three locations in Hong Kong.<\\/em><\\/p>\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"margin-top: 0px; margin-left: -1.5px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 2.2rem; color: #1c1c1c; letter-spacing: 1.5px; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; overflow-wrap: break-word;\\\">5. Top Schools<\\/h3>\\r\\n<figure id=\\\"attachment_178823\\\" class=\\\"wp-caption aligncenter\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px auto 28px; max-width: 100%; clear: both; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; width: 900px;\\\" aria-describedby=\\\"caption-attachment-178823\\\"><img class=\\\"size-medium wp-image-178823 lazyloaded\\\" style=\\\"border: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 1000ms ease 0ms; min-width: 100%; margin: 0px auto;\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/76615116_2740710342658505_1148822301920198656_n-900x643.jpeg\\\" sizes=\\\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\\\" srcset=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/76615116_2740710342658505_1148822301920198656_n-900x643.jpeg 900w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/76615116_2740710342658505_1148822301920198656_n-768x549.jpeg 768w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/76615116_2740710342658505_1148822301920198656_n.jpeg 1400w\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" width=\\\"900\\\" height=\\\"643\\\" data-srcset=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/76615116_2740710342658505_1148822301920198656_n-900x643.jpeg 900w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/76615116_2740710342658505_1148822301920198656_n-768x549.jpeg 768w, https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/76615116_2740710342658505_1148822301920198656_n.jpeg 1400w\\\" data-src=\\\"https:\\/\\/static.thehoneycombers.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/sites\\/6\\/2021\\/04\\/76615116_2740710342658505_1148822301920198656_n-900x643.jpeg\\\" data-sizes=\\\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<figcaption id=\\\"caption-attachment-178823\\\" class=\\\"wp-caption-text\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 1.4rem; text-align: center; color: #2db3b1; padding: 5px 0px;\\\">(Photography: Top Schools via Facebook)<\\/figcaption>\\r\\n<\\/figure>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Perfect for parents who might be moving around Asia a lot, Top Schools specialises in placing students in international schools in Hong Kong, Singapore, and Malaysia, as well as state, boarding, and private schools in the UK.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 28px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Getting into these schools can be complicated, but Top Schools simplifies the process with personalised admissions consulting, advice on budgeting and debentures, and even support for assessments and tutoring. Right now, you can even take advantage of their BNO Relocations plans which offer support for transferring kids to a British school in the UK under the BNO scheme.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #333333; font-family: adelle-sans, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\"><em><a style=\\\"color: #e84625; background-image: initial; background-position: 0px 0px; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; transition: all 0.1s ease-in-out 0s; border: 0px; border-radius: 0px !important;\\\" title=\\\"\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.topschools.asia\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow noopener\\\" data-original-title=\\\"\\\">Top Schools<\\/a>, 14\\/F Yue Shing Commercial Building, 15 Queen Victoria Street, Central, Hong Kong. p. 3565 5866&nbsp;<\\/em><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"At Foundation, the goal is to find the best educational fit for your child. The team brings decades of experience to bear in placing your child in the right international school, boarding school, or university\\u2014and they even offer help for summer schools, too. If your child is planning a non-traditional route for university, Foundation can help, too\\u2014their Accelerating Athletes Program can help aspiring athletes get into an NCAA school in the US or perhaps rowing for Oxford at Henley, while their services for gifted\\/learning differences students offer support for students with special educational needs.\"}', '18191644673008.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'the-best-education-consultants-in-hong-kong', 1, NULL, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `excerpt`, `feature_img_name`, `feature_img_original_name`, `feature_img_mime`, `feature_img_ext`, `status`, `tags`, `read`, `headline`, `front_slider`, `highlight`, `publish_status`, `published_year`, `published_number`, `published_at`, `slug`, `addedby_id`, `writer_id`, `editedby_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(25, '{\"en\":\"We are the British Education Consultants Ltd\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(34, 31, 31); font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">We are the British Education Consultants Ltd, We are one of the leading consultancy services for education in the United Kingdom. We are enthusiastic about learning and education in general. We provide free, honest, independent and informative advice and guidance to all types and levels of education and training needs, to national and international learners who are interested in studying in the UK. We will take your hand from overseas to study in the UK, until we wave you good by when you finish your amazing educational journey.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(34, 31, 31); font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">We also have a great experience and know-how to UK educational system. Prospective student and trainees will get the full benefit of what we provide as we always stay close to our clients through the whole process from submitting your schools, colleges, universities and training application, your English language needs, Visa application, any issues or advise regarding the fees and payments to the education provider.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(34, 31, 31); font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Our company and its consultants are certified by the British Council to provide the best educational advice and guidance to UK and international students who are studying or are planning to study in the UK. We have a great relationship with many universities and educational institutions and our application success rate is high. We don\\u2019t let our clients apply by themselves, our expert admission department will provide all the help needed to guarantee your seat and will make the application process easier for our clients.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(34, 31, 31); font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">We are one of the fastest-growing educational consultancies and are committed to setting the exceptional standards of service. Our free consultants work with you every step of the way to find the university that is right for you and will guide you through the entire application process. With our tireless efforts, we help students attain offers from universities such as Medicine, Nursing, Art &amp; Design, Project Management, International Relations, Business &amp; Management, and History.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(34, 31, 31); font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Whatever degree program you may choose, we help you find a course at the budget of your convenience in the subject you\\u2019re interested in with our affiliated colleges and universities. Choosing the right course is a very important decision because it sets foundation for your future path. This is why our aim is to make you ready for your career and help you choose the right program to study and develop your career path, including internship and work placement offers.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(34, 31, 31); font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">We understand that the COVID-19 pandemic has changed education forever. Educational needs and the increase of virtual and online courses has surged exponentially. We believe that we can help you to gain access to the UK educational providers to meet those needs.<\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(34, 31, 31); font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Our British Council certification number is&nbsp; (agent Ref: GAL\\/16807). We are based on Berkeley Suite, 35 Berkeley Square, Mayfair London W1J 5BF. Our company is registered at the UK Companies House, (registration number: 11303282).<\\/p><h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(23, 126, 195); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.3; margin-top: 0px; font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\\\"><strong style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\\\">Our aims and objectives are:<\\/strong><\\/h3><ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(34, 31, 31); font-family: Muli, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\"><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; padding: 3px 0px 3px 22px;\\\">Provide students with trusted advice and guidance on educational, academic and training courses relevant to their needs.<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; padding: 3px 0px 3px 22px;\\\">Be completely informed about our affiliated and partner institutes in order to help students choose the best place to study.<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; padding: 3px 0px 3px 22px;\\\">Assist students with their VISA applications, and providing them clear guidance about legal restrictions applicable to them.<\\/li><li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; padding: 3px 0px 3px 22px;\\\">Helping students make the transition from home to international country to pursue education<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}', '{\"en\":\"We are the British Education Consultants Ltd, We are one of the leading consultancy services for education in the United Kingdom. We are enthusiastic about learning and education in general. We provide free, honest, independent and informative advice and guidance to all types and levels of education and training needs, to national and international learners who are interested in studying in the UK. We will take your hand from overseas to study in the UK, until we wave you good by when you finish your amazing educational journey.\"}', '61491644673246.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'we-are-the-british-education-consultants-ltd', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(26, '{\"en\":\"Sheds, halls and flat warehouses\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p><font style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; color: rgb(33, 50, 58); font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13.8662px; text-align: justify; vertical-align: inherit;\\\"><font style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">In complex FEERUM drying and storage units, sheds are most often used at the point of receipt or collection of grain, as a cover for the charging hopper.&nbsp;<\\/font><font style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Depending on the destination - we design, manufacture and build flat warehouses that serve as a place for storing grain, and halls where machines and other materials can be stored.<\\/font><\\/font><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; color: rgb(33, 50, 58); font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13.8662px; text-align: justify;\\\"><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"In complex FEERUM drying and storage units, sheds are most often used at the point of receipt or collection of grain, as a cover for the charging hopper.\"}', '87061644825046.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'sheds-halls-and-flat-warehouses', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(27, '{\"en\":\"Armature\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; font-size: 1.0833em; line-height: 1.6666; color: #21323a; font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">All FEERUM devices and technological connections are made&nbsp;<\\/span><strong style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; font-weight: bold;\\\">of hot-dip galvanized steel<\\/strong><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">&nbsp;with a wall thickness of 3 mm and 4 mm<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<table style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; border-spacing: 0px; max-width: 100%; color: #21323a; font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px; text-align: justify; white-space: normal;\\\" width=\\\"100%\\\">\\r\\n<tbody style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"2%\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" width=\\\"98%\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Electric, pneumatic and manual distributors<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Pipes, elbows, reductions, symmetrical and asymmetrical tees and crosses<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Forwarding Rotary Rings<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Vertical brakes (maintenance free)<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Angle brakes (maintenance-free)<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Electric, pneumatic and manual valves<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Dust lock<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Percentage selector<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; vertical-align: inherit;\\\">Efficiency controller<\\/span><\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody>\\r\\n<\\/table>\"}', '{\"en\":\"All FEERUM devices and technological connections are made of hot-dip galvanized steel with a wall thickness of 3 mm and 4 mm\"}', 'armature_381644825150.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'armature', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(28, '{\"en\":\"Transaction notifications\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h1 class=\\\"entry-title\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; font-size: 2em; font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.25em; color: #2d3e52; text-align: justify;\\\">Market Abuse Regulation<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color: #21323a; font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px; text-align: justify;\\\">In connection with the entry into force on 3 July 2016 of Regulation (EU) No 596\\/2014 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16 April 2014 on market abuse (Regulation on market abuse) and repealing Directive 2003\\/6 \\/ WE of the European Parliament and of the Council and Commission Directives 2003\\/124 \\/ EC, 2003\\/125 \\/ EC and 2004\\/72 \\/ EC (\\\"MAR Regulation\\\") persons closely related to the Members of the Management Board and Members of the Supervisory Board of FEERUM SA are obliged to notify the Company and the Polish Financial Supervision Authority about transactions made on own account on FEERUM SA financial instruments.<\\/span><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; color: #21323a; font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px; text-align: justify;\\\" \\/><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; color: #21323a; font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px; text-align: justify;\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n<h1 class=\\\"entry-title\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; font-size: 2em; font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.25em; color: #2d3e52; text-align: justify;\\\">Notification procedure<\\/h1>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"post-content\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; color: #21323a; font-family: Lato, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px; text-align: justify;\\\">\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; font-family: inherit; line-height: 1.2222em; color: #2d3e52; font-size: 1.5em;\\\">A scan of signed notifications should be sent by e-mail:<\\/h3>\\r\\n1. to FEERUM S.A. to the address: relacjeinwestorskie@feerum.pl<br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/>and<br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/>2. to the Polish Financial Supervision Authority to the following address:&nbsp;<a style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" href=\\\"mailto:notyfikacje.art.19mar@knf.gov.pl\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; color: f08300;\\\">notyfikacje.art.19mar@knf.gov.pl<\\/span><\\/a><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; font-family: inherit; line-height: 1.2222em; color: #2d3e52; font-size: 1.5em;\\\">Files to download<\\/h3>\\r\\n<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; color: f08300;\\\">&bull;&nbsp;<a style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.knf.gov.pl\\/en\\/ABOUT_US\\/International_cooperation\\/EU\\/EU_regulations\\/MAD\\\">SPOSITION OF THE OFFICE OF THE FINANCIAL SUPERVISION AUTHORITY COMMISSION ON THE METHOD OF COMPLETING NOTIFICATIONS ON TRANSACTIONS<\\/a><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/><\\/span><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; color: f08300;\\\">&bull;&nbsp;<a style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/feerum.pl\\/dokumenty\\/Formularz%20zg%C5%82aszania%20transakcji.docx\\\">NOTIFICATION FORM FOR TRANSACTIONS ON FEERUM FINANCIAL INSTRUMENTS<\\/a><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/><\\/span><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/>\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1; font-family: inherit; line-height: 1.2222em; color: #2d3e52; font-size: 1.5em;\\\">A closely related person means:<\\/h3>\\r\\na) spouse;<br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/>b) a dependent child in accordance with national law;<br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/>c) ) a family member who remains in the common household on the day of the transaction for a period of at least one year;<br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; zoom: 1;\\\" \\/>d) a legal person, a group of enterprises or a partnership, in which the managerial duties are fulfilled by a member of the FEERUM SA Management Board or Supervisory Board. or the person referred to in point a), b) or c), over which such person exercises direct or indirect control, which was created to benefit the person or whose economic interests are largely consistent with the interests of such a person.<\\/div>\"}', '{\"en\":\"In connection with the entry into force on 3 July 2016 of Regulation (EU) No 596\\/2014 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16 April 2014 on market abuse (Regulation on market abuse) and repealing Directive 2003\\/6 \\/ WE of the European Parliament and of the Council and Commission Directives 2003\\/124 \\/ EC, 2003\\/125 \\/ EC and 2004\\/72 \\/ EC (\\\"MAR Regulation\\\") persons closely related to the Members of the Management Board and Members of the Supervisory Board of FEERUM SA are obliged to notify the Company and the Polish Financial Supervision Authority about transactions made on own account on FEERUM SA financial instruments.\"}', '94281644825874.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'transaction-notifications', 1, NULL, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(29, '{\"en\":\"Company Profile\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p><strong style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">Plug LTD<\\/strong><span style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;has been incepted in the year 2005 by the well known reputed professional Bangladeshi businessman Mr. Md. Ismail Hossain. It is mainly deal with Import-Export of machineries and parts especially imports and trading flour milling rolls from Poland. Since incorporation it has been&nbsp;<\\/span><strong style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">Exclusive Sole Agent<\\/strong><span style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;for&nbsp;<\\/span><strong style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">FP Spomax S.A.<\\/strong><span style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">, Poland in Bangladesh.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<div style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">\\r\\n<div style=\\\"float: left; width: 670px;\\\"><br \\/>In 1982, Mr. Hossain introduced flour mill rolls in Bangladesh from Poland. He is the pioneer to sell Polish rolls in Bangladesh, at that time he worked for the company namely&nbsp;<strong>Azad and Company Ltd.<\\/strong>&nbsp;and he was the Managing Director of the said company. Later the company has been abolished and he worked for his self owned proprietorship company&nbsp;<strong>Azad and Company.<\\/strong><\\/div>\\r\\n<div style=\\\"clear: both;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">Later on he established a limited company namely&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-weight: bolder; color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">Plug LTD<\\/span><span style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;where he is the&nbsp;<\\/span><strong style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">Managing Director.<\\/strong><span style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;With his professional skills he diversified this business countrywide successfully. Being a communist overwhelmed country it was very difficult to trade with Poland in early 80&rsquo;s though Mr. Hossain continued his business with his professionalism. This company has highly skilled employees and now an active full-fledged Trading House procuring\\/sourcing various types of machineries and spare parts from Europe notably from Poland and also largest importer from Poland in Bangladesh.<\\/span><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Plug LTD has been incepted in the year 2005 by the well known reputed professional Bangladeshi businessman Mr. Md. Ismail Hossain. It is mainly deal with Import-Export of machineries and parts especially imports and trading flour milling rolls from Poland. Since incorporation it has been Exclusive Sole Agent for FP Spomax S.A., Poland in Bangladesh.\"}', '39931644830951.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 0, 0, 'draft', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'company-profile', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(30, '{\"en\":\"FP Spomax S.A.\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h3 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\\\">FP Spomax S.A.<\\/h3><p><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">In&nbsp;<\\/span><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">1882<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">, Ernst Arnold Machin began to build factories for Agriculture. The company was manufacturing machines for threshing grain crops and agricultural tools . Then it has been revolutionized by time as follows\\u2026\\u2026<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">1905<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;The creation of an iron foundry.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">1950--1959<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;The modernization of the factory, a five-fold increase in production.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">1967--1975<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;Construction of an iron foundry and production hall with an area of 6560 square meters.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">1981<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;Change the name of the Machinery and Equipment Factory for Food Industry as SPOMASZ.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">1985<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;Start of implementation of computer technology.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">1990<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;Purchase of technology and equipment for centrifugal casting rolls.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">1995<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;Start of privatization.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">2000<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;Strategic investor: FP Engineering Ltd.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\"><b style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">2003<\\/b><span style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: UbuntuMedium, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\\\">&nbsp;Change of company name as FP SPOMAX S.A.<\\/span><br><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"In 1882, Ernst Arnold Machin began to build factories for Agriculture. The company was manufacturing machines for threshing grain crops and agricultural tools . Then it has been revolutionized by time as follows\\u2026\\u2026\"}', '36531644831099.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'fp-spomax-s-a', 1, NULL, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(31, '{\"en\":\"History\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>In 1882 Ernst Arnold began the erection of Fabryka Machin DLA\\r\\nRolnictwa (Factory of Machines for Agriculture). The company\\r\\nmanufactured machines for corn growing, threshing and farm\\r\\ntools.\\r\\nIt was the intention of the owners to constantly develop and\\r\\nmodernize the company. In 1905 the foundry was established\\r\\nand in the next few years, the number of employees grew to 150\\r\\npeople.\\r\\nThe thirties saw a big boom in the production of milling machinery.\\r\\nThe company under the new name Fabryka Maszyn M\\u00b3y\\u00f1skich\\r\\n(Factory for Milling Machines) manufactured an almost a full range\\r\\nof machines for the flour milling industry. It offered also assembly and service.\\r\\nA new important stage in the history of our company which\\r\\nbrought about its further development after World War II\\r\\nwas modernization and introduction of new technologies.\\r\\nDuringthefollowingyearsthesubsequentgenerationsofhighly\\r\\nmotivated and dedicated workers have earned a worldwide reputation.\\r\\nConstant innovations and creativity allowed FP SPOMAX to\\r\\ndevelop individual solutions according to the needs of our\\r\\nFP SPOMAX\\r\\nclients. The research department has always been considered as\\r\\nan indispensable factor of the company\'s success. FP SPOMAX\\r\\nwidened its production program and acquired experience to\\r\\nbecome a specialist in the flourm illingfield.\\r\\nFP SPOMAX is a medium-size private company with an\\r\\nestablished market position. We pride ourselves on being able\\r\\nto offer full customer service, ranging from consultation to commissioning sites.\\r\\nBased on 120 years experience FP SPOMAX is able to offer the\\r\\nhighest quality product tailored to suit individual clients needs,\\r\\nreliable, allowing quick and safe recovery of investments<br><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"In 1882 Ernst Arnold began the erection of Fabryka Machin DLA Rolnictwa (Factory of Machines for Agriculture). The company manufactured machines for corn growing, threshing and farm tools. It was the intention of the owners to constantly develop and modernize the company.\"}', '84121644831485.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'history', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(32, '{\"en\":\"Roots\' type blowers \\/ Dmuchawy typu Roots\'a\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>The research department continuously expands on the range of\\r\\noffered products. This is done with our clients in mind, their\\r\\nsatisfaction is of highest importance. Our blowers are\\r\\ncharacterized by high quality and reliability, even in the most\\r\\nextreme conditions.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>The blower components are manufactured with the highest\\r\\nprecision on modern CNC machining centres. We offer a range of\\r\\nproduct that meets all requirements set for blowers packages,\\r\\nwhich include their resistance, reliability, efficiency and noise\\r\\nabsorption.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Elementy dmuchaw produkowane s\\u00b9 z najwi\\u00eaksz\\u00b9 precyzj\\u00b9 na\\r\\nnajnowszej generacji centrach obr\\u00f3bczych. Oferujemy produkt\\r\\nspe\\u00b3niaj\\u00b9cy wszystkie wymagania stawiane agregatom\\r\\ndmuchaw odno\\u0153nie ich trwa\\u00b3o\\u0153ci, niezawodno\\u0153ci, sprawno\\u0153ci,\\r\\njak r\\u00f3wnie\\u00bf t\\u00b3umienia d\\u0178wi\\u00eak\\u00f3w.<br><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"The research department continuously expands on the range of offered products.\"}', '96261644831710.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'roots-type-blowers-dmuchawy-typu-roots-a', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(33, '{\"en\":\"Roll casting\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>Roll casting FP SPOMAX rolls are produced in our own foundry in one of the most modern centrifugal casting lines in Europe. The chemical composition of each roll is checked during the casting process and each case is individually numbered. The process of centrifugal casting enables us to maintain full control over the casting procedure and ensures uniformity of the hard layer of the rolls. As a result, SPORTMAX offers a high-quality product that can be used for many years. Roll machining After casting, the rolls are cut to the required length and machined according to the individual requirements of each customer. Roll fluting is done using single point fluting machines and each roll is dynamically balanced. Finished rolls are subject to extensive quality control procedures, in which the measurements are compared with the received order. A certificate containing this comparison is supplied with each roll. Quality control FP SPOMAX has implemented ISO 9001 quality management system which includes a complete product identification scheme at every stage of the production process. Each roll comes with its own individual serial number which allows us to identify every roll made by SPORTMAX. Full records of the roll, including chemical composition, hardness, dimensions, finish, manufacturing date and the name of the customer are kept at SPOMAX for 10 years.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Roll casting FP SPOMAX rolls are produced in our own foundry in one of the most modern centrifugal casting lines in Europe. The chemical composition of each roll is checked during the casting process and each case is individually numbered. The process of centrifugal casting enables us to maintain full control over the casting procedure and ensures uniformity of the hard layer of the rolls.\"}', 'roll-casting_381644834057.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'roll-casting', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(34, '{\"en\":\"Airlock SLU\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>Construction<\\/p><p>\\r\\nBasic elements of airlock are:\\r\\n- cast iron body with rectangular inlet and outlet\\r\\nopenings,\\r\\n- cast iron rotor installed inside the body,\\r\\n- side covers with pressure bearings, sealing rings\\r\\nand bearing covers,\\r\\nAirlocks are manufactured in two versions:\\r\\n- independent (moto-reducer) marked with M\\r\\n(power in table)\\r\\n- group (2-8 pcs) driven via shaft(s), motor reducer and clutches (installed power max 1,5 kW\\r\\ndepending on airlock number).<\\/p><hr><p>Operation<\\/p><p>Product is directed to the inlet of the airlock and as a\\r\\nresult of rotor\'s revolutions it is evenly fed to the\\r\\noutlet, simultaneously cutting off the airflow from\\r\\nthe pneumatic conveying systems<br><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Basic elements of airlock are: - cast iron body with rectangular inlet and outlet openings, - cast iron rotor installed inside the body,\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'airlock-slu', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(35, '{\"en\":\"Application Double Deck Dry Destoner\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>Application Double Deck Dry Destoner is a modern grain cleaning machine. The features include high performance, small overall dimensions and low power and air consumption. Due to two sieve decks, the machine is able to separate grain into two fractions: heavy and light, with simultaneous separation of higher density material such as stones, pieces of metal and glass from corn or other grain products.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Construction<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Basic assemblies of the Double Deck Dry Destoner include: &bull; body with installed sifting frames (frames dimensions for SOK-15K: width =1245 mm, length =1100 mm; for SOK-20K: width =1445 mm, length =1300 mm); frames are protected with bars allowing easy inserting and taking out of sifting frames; body elements also include: - product outlet: - light fraction &ldquo;b&rdquo;, - heavy fraction &ldquo;c&rdquo;, - stone outlet &ldquo;e&rdquo;, &bull; cover with sight glasses to observe sieve operation, &bull; product inlet with flap valve regulated by return spring, &bull; supporting frame with shock absorbers, &bull; drive assembly inducing vibratory movement of the device, &bull; supporting structure with installed: - product inlet pipe &ldquo;a&rdquo;, - air outlet &ldquo;d&rdquo; with regulated flap by means of regulating assembly, - manometer, &bull; outlet channel, &bull; stone container.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Operation<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Product intended for cleaning is gravitationally fed through the inlet to the top sieve. The product, through directing elements located in the cover, is uniformly distributed on the whole sieve&rsquo;s width. Due to vibratory movement and impact of even air stream passing from down to the top through both sieves and forming air cushions over top and bottom sieve, the product is spread on the whole sieve surface. Air cushion created over the top sieve lifts the light fraction to the outlet &ldquo;b&rdquo;, heavy fraction and stones get through top sieve perforated sheet metal wholes to the bottom sieve lapped with wire mesh. On the bottom sieve, air cushion lifting the product, that is transported to the outlet &ldquo;c&rdquo;, allows stones that contact the sieve due to vibratory movement, to move upwards to the outlet &ldquo;e&rdquo;. In order to achieve optimum selection rate, inclination angle and air quantity can be adjusted, as needed.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Manufacturer reserves the right for modifications of parameters and device appearance in the course of its improvement.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Application Double Deck Dry Destoner is a modern grain cleaning machine. The features include high performance, small overall dimensions and low power and air consumption. Due to two sieve decks, the machine is able to separate grain into two fractions: heavy and light, with simultaneous separation of higher density material such as stones, pieces of metal and glass from corn or other grain products.\"}', '27131644832803.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'application-double-deck-dry-destoner', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(36, '{\"en\":\"SCOURING MACHINE\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>Application\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Double Deck Dry Destoner is a modern grain cleaning machine. The features include high\\r\\nperformance, small overall dimensions and low power and air consumption. Due to two sieve decks,\\r\\nthe machine is able to separate grain into two fractions: heavy and light, with simultaneous\\r\\nseparation of higher density material such as stones, pieces of metal and glass from corn or other\\r\\ngrain products.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p> Construction\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Basic assemblies of the Double Deck Dry Destoner include:\\r\\n\\u2022 body with installed sifting frames (frames dimensions for SOK-15K: width =1245 mm, length\\r\\n=1100 mm; for SOK-20K: width =1445 mm, length =1300 mm); frames are protected with\\r\\nbars allowing easy inserting and taking out of sifting frames; body elements also include:\\r\\n- product outlet:\\r\\n- light fraction \\u201cb\\u201d,\\r\\n- heavy fraction \\u201cc\\u201d,\\r\\n- stone outlet \\u201ce\\u201d,\\r\\n\\u2022 cover with sight glasses to observe sieve operation,\\r\\n\\u2022 product inlet with flap valve regulated by return spring,\\r\\n\\u2022 supporting frame with shock absorbers,\\r\\n\\u2022 drive assembly inducing vibratory movement of the device,\\r\\n\\u2022 supporting structure with installed:\\r\\n- product inlet pipe \\u201ca\\u201d,\\r\\n- air outlet \\u201cd\\u201d with regulated flap by means of regulating assembly,\\r\\n- manometer,\\r\\n\\u2022 outlet channel,\\r\\n\\u2022 stone container.<\\/p><p>Operation\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Product intended for cleaning is gravitationally fed through the inlet to the top sieve. The product,\\r\\nthrough directing elements located in the cover, is uniformly distributed on the whole sieve\\u2019s width. Due\\r\\nto vibratory movement and impact of even air stream passing from down to the top through both sieves\\r\\nand forming air cushions over top and bottom sieve, the product is spread on the whole sieve surface. Air\\r\\ncushion created over the top sieve lifts the light fraction to the outlet \\u201cb\\u201d, heavy fraction and stones get\\r\\nthrough top sieve perforated sheet metal wholes to the bottom sieve lapped with wire mesh. On the\\r\\nbottom sieve, air cushion lifting the product, that is transported to the outlet \\u201cc\\u201d, allows stones that\\r\\ncontact the sieve due to vibratory movement, to move upwards to the outlet \\u201ce\\u201d.\\r\\nIn order to achieve optimum selection rate, inclination angle and air quantity can be adjusted, as\\r\\nneeded.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>Manufacturer reserves the right for modifications of parameters and device appearance in the course\\r\\nof its improvement.&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Double Deck Dry Destoner is a modern grain cleaning machine. The features include high performance, small overall dimensions and low power and air consumption.\"}', '68981644833951.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'scouring-machine', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `excerpt`, `feature_img_name`, `feature_img_original_name`, `feature_img_mime`, `feature_img_ext`, `status`, `tags`, `read`, `headline`, `front_slider`, `highlight`, `publish_status`, `published_year`, `published_number`, `published_at`, `slug`, `addedby_id`, `writer_id`, `editedby_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(37, '{\"en\":\"EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>RATIONAL OF THIS PROJECT<br><\\/p><p>Tourism is one of the worlds\\u2019 fastest growing \\r\\nindustries. It entails activities and services \\r\\nassociated with transportation, \\r\\naccommodation, food, shopping, entertainment \\r\\nand hospitality services available for the \\r\\ntravellers. Tourism is a major source of income \\r\\ngeneration and foreign exchange earnings in \\r\\nmany countries. It creates ample job \\r\\nopportunities and plays a pivotal role in country \\r\\nbranding. With the advent of today\\u2019s \\r\\nglobalization, immense technological \\r\\nadvancement, socio-demographic factors and \\r\\nrapid urbanization, the tourism sector is \\r\\nchanging fast. Hence it has become multi\\u0002dimensional. UNWTO (United Nations World \\r\\nTourism Organization) defines Tourism as \\u201cthe \\r\\nactivities of the persons travelling to and staying \\r\\nin places outside their usual environment for not \\r\\nmore than one consecutive year for leisure, \\r\\nbusiness or other purposes\\u201d. Bangladesh, which \\r\\nwas once termed by cynics a \\\"bottomless \\r\\nbasket\\\" has now become a \\\"basket full of \\r\\nwonders.\\\" The country with its limited resources \\r\\nhas been maintaining 8% annual average GDP \\r\\ngrowth rate and has brought about remarkable \\r\\nsocial and human development.\\r\\nWhen people become weary of living a \\r\\nmonotonous life in the concrete city, they prefer \\r\\nto spend some time, especially during the \\r\\nweekends, amid natural serenity. As cities \\r\\nbecome more crowded and polluted, peoples\' \\r\\ndemand for breathing space also increases.\\r\\nThis demand has led to development of a robust \\r\\nresort industry in Bangladesh in the last decade. \\r\\nThe growing economy of the country and the \\r\\nrising purchasing power of consumers have \\r\\nmade the industry commercially viable.\\r\\nAccording to the Bangladesh Parjatan \\r\\nCorporation (BPC), around 200 resorts have \\r\\nbeen built across the country especially in the \\r\\nsurrounding areas of the capital like Gazipur, \\r\\nNarayanganj and Narsingdi\\r\\nFor meet the fastest growing demand of \\r\\ntourism industry, Shitalakhya Water Kingdom\\r\\nhas taken initiative to setup Amusement park \\r\\nand resort project in Rupgonj, Narayangonj,\\r\\nBangladesh. Due to increasing trend in\\r\\nrecent years, this project is highly profitable.\\r\\nThe total service revenue capacity of the unit \\r\\nwill be BDT 47.49 Crore per year, however, 1st\\r\\nyear revenue will be 39.68 Crore. The \\r\\nproposed Amusement Park involves a total \\r\\ninvestment of about BDT 1,429.08 million. \\r\\nThis includes capital investment 1,305.55 \\r\\nmillion and BDT 78.25 million as initial \\r\\nworking capital and BDT 45.27 million as \\r\\nIDCP.\\r\\nThe proposed project will be financed through \\r\\n36% debt and 64% equity for long term \\r\\nfinance. The Net Present Value (NPV) of the \\r\\nproject is around BDT 471.83 million with an \\r\\nInternal Rate of Return (IRR) of 19% and a \\r\\npayback period of 5.98 years.\\r\\nThe project will provide employment \\r\\nopportunities to 130 people. Finally, the \\r\\nmanagement of Company has vast knowledge \\r\\nand experience in business areas especially in \\r\\nthe Service sector.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Tourism is one of the worlds\\u2019 fastest growing industries. It entails activities and services associated with transportation, accommodation, food, shopping, entertainment and hospitality services available for the travellers.\"}', '12691644834588.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'executive-summary', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(38, '{\"en\":\"DECLARATIONS AND DUE DILIGENCE CERTIFICATE\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>DECLARATION ABOUT THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE PROPRIETOR OF\\r\\nTHE CONCERN \\u201cM\\/S SHITALAKHYA WATER KINGDOM\\u201d IN RESPECT OF\\r\\nTHIS FEASIBLITY REPORT.\\r\\nThe feasibility report has been prepared, seen and approved by us, and we, individually\\r\\nand collectively, accept full responsibility for the authenticity and accuracy of the\\r\\nstatements made, information give in the report, documents, projected financial\\r\\nstatements, exhibits, annexes, papers submitted to the your financial institution in\\r\\nsupport thereof, and this report has been met and that there are no other information or\\r\\ndocuments the omission or which make any information of statements therein\\r\\nmisleading for which the respective financial institutions may take any civil, criminal of\\r\\nadministrative action against any of all of us as it may deem fit.\\r\\nWe also confirm that full and fair disclosure has been made in this report to enable the\\r\\ninvestors or financial institution to make a well-informed decision for investment.\\r\\nFardous Ahamad Badal\\r\\nProprietor\\r\\nM\\/S SHITALAKHYA WATER KINGDOM&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"DECLARATION ABOUT THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE PROPRIETOR OF THE CONCERN \\u201cM\\/S SHITALAKHYA WATER KINGDOM\\u201d IN RESPECT OF THIS FEASIBLITY REPORT.\"}', '14381644834787.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'declarations-and-due-diligence-certificate', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(39, '{\"en\":\"Brief Description of Project & Product\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>Due to huge potentials of the amusement park of Bangladesh and sizeable market, M\\/S SHITALAKHYA WATER KINGDOM has planned to establish a Asumement park named Shitalakhya Water Kingdom. In this park, there will be various types of rides such as Train, Merry-go-Round, Ferris Wheel, Game Zone and Water Park rides. Water park rides will include Speed Boat, Combo Boat, Inflatable Boat, Rib Boat, Barbecue Boat, Bumper Boat, Water Car, Lover boat, Yellow Boat, Tricycle (Double), Tricycle (Single) and Jet Sky. In Water World, there will be rainbow slides, wave pool, water dancing &amp; other rides. Besides, there will also be swimming pool, resort and gymnasium. There will be total Fourty-four (44) rides in which there will be one (01) train, one (01) merry-go-round, one (01) ferris wheel, five (05) Game Zones and thirty (30) others park rides. Besides, there will be twenty (20) cottages and 3 Convention centre and the occupancy rate has been estimated 30.00% in first year with 10.00% growth every year. For restaurant and food court, visitors have been estimated 720,000 per year with 10.00% growth every year and each visitor spending\\/day has been estimated BDT 100.00. Yearly revenue operational days has been estimated 100 days within 360 days.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The total project cost has been estimated BDT 1,429.08 mln in which fixed costs BDT 1,305.55 mln, IDCP BDT 78.25 &amp; variable costs BDT 45.27 mln. The five years&rsquo; average sales revenue has been projected BDT 469.17 mln. &nbsp;<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Due to huge potentials of the amusement park of Bangladesh and sizeable market, M\\/S SHITALAKHYA WATER KINGDOM has planned to establish a Asumement park named Shitalakhya Water Kingdom.\"}', 'brief-description-of-project-product_771644834954.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'brief-description-of-project-product-2', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(40, '{\"en\":\"Demographic Analysis of Dhaka, Narayangonj, Garzipur District\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p>Dhaka District:<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Dhaka District (Bengali: \\u09a2\\u09be\\u0995\\u09be $\\u099c\\u09b2\\u09be, Dhaka jela) is a district in central Bangladesh. It is a part of the Dhaka Division. Dhaka, the capital of Bangladesh, rests on the eastern banks of the Buriganga River which flows from the Turag to the south of the district. While Dhaka (city corporation) occupies only about a fifth of the area of Dhaka district, it is the economic, political, and cultural centre of the district and the country as a whole. Dhaka district consists of Dhaka city, Keraniganj, Nababganj, Dohar, Savar, and Dhamrai upazila. Dhaka District is an administrative entity, and like many other cities, it does not cover the modern conurbation which is Greater Dhaka, which has spilled into neighbouring districts, nor does the conurbation cover the whole district, as there are rural areas within the district. Gazipur District: Gazipur District is located at just north of capital city of Dhaka, Bangladesh. The previous name of the region is &ldquo;Joydebpur&rdquo;. Once, the region was under the deep jungle of Vowal Pargana (Sub- Division). Gazipur district is one of the ancient and historical region with hundreds years old tradition. Sakeswar Monument of emperor Ashok period, Dardia fort of Mourja period, Buddhist Monastery of the king Dhol Samudra reminds us the history of 2500 years ago. The first Bengali dictionary and grammar and the first printed book of prose (1733) was written by Portugal priests in the region. Besides the best Muslin (very thin fabrics) of the country was produced in Titbati village in Kapashia that was very popular throughout the world. During the liberation war, first armed defence was introduced from the region in 19 March. There are 19 KPI, 05 universities, the one and only High- Tech Park of the country and a number of government, semi government and private offices and industries.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Narayangonj District:<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>(Bengali: \\u09a8\\u09be\\u09b0\\u09be\\u09df\\u09a3\\u0997,, romanized: Narayo\\u1e47gonj) is a district in central Bangladesh which is a part of the Dhaka Division.[1] It is home to the ancient city of Sonargaon and is one of the oldest industrial districts in the country. The district lies on the banks of the Delete and the Sheetolokkha River. It is an industrial hub and plays an important part in the country\'s jute trade, plant processing and sector. It is nicknamed the \\\"Dundee of Bangladesh\\\" due to the presence of many jute mills.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Total Land size of this project is Total 9.54 acres.\"}', 'demographic-analysis-of-dhaka-narayangonj-garzipur-district_841644835867.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'demographic-analysis-of-dhaka-narayangonj-garzipur-district', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(41, '{\"en\":\"Benefits of LPG\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h5 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 3.5em; margin-bottom: 1.75em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 900; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3125; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000;\\\">#&nbsp; &nbsp; What is LPG?<\\/h5>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: #000000;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify;\\\">LPG is the short name for Liquefied Petroleum Gas, this is a mixture of Propane and Butane extracted from Gas &amp; Oil fields. LPG is a clean fuel that has a range of properties closest to Octane. LPG is the third most popular automotive fuel in the world.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h5 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 3.5em; margin-bottom: 1.75em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 900; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3125; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000;\\\">#&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Is it Safe?<\\/h5>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: #000000;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1em; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">LPG has an excellent safety record throughout the world, in storage, transportation and use. LPG is stored inside tank at 20 times less pressure than CNG!<\\/span><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1em; font-family: verdana, geneva; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1em; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\\" \\/><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h5 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 3.5em; margin-bottom: 1.75em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 900; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3125; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000;\\\">#&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Is LPG Conversion Costly?<\\/h5>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: #000000;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify;\\\">Converting into LPG is cheaper than the cost of CNG conversion. A standard Sequential Injection LPG Conversion costs in the range of 55000 &ndash; 60000!<span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1em; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1em; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><br style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box;\\\" \\/><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h5 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 3.5em; margin-bottom: 1.75em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 900; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3125; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000;\\\">#&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Will I save money using LPG?<\\/h5>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: #000000;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify;\\\">Yes, with an LPG conversion you will save money as soon as you drive away. With the price of LPG (@42\\/Ltr) being approx 50% less than octane (@89\\/Ltr), you will start saving 45% for traveling the same distance!<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h5 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 3.5em; margin-bottom: 1.75em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 900; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3125; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000;\\\">#&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;What mileage will I get on LPG?<\\/h5>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: #000000;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify;\\\">Theoretically LPG will give you 85-90% of the mileage that you would travel on the same quantity of octane. eg: If 1 litre of octane took you 10 km, then 1 litre of LPG would take you 8.5-9 km. But practically in Bangladesh, LPG mileage is at around 5% less than the mileage of Octane just because of the contamination of Octane!<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h5 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 3.5em; margin-bottom: 1.75em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 900; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3125; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000;\\\">#&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Which LPG system is recommended?<\\/h5>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: #000000;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify;\\\"><strong style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bold; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\\\">Sequential Injection system<\\/strong>&nbsp;is the only recommended system for LPG conversion for modern vehicles. It ensures the correct mileage &amp; smooth acceleration of the car. Tuning &amp; calibration are done with the help of dedicated software for LPG system and no frequent tuning is required.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h5 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 3.5em; margin-bottom: 1.75em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 900; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3125; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #000000;\\\">#&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Can LPG damage my engine?<\\/h5>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 40px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: #000000;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: justify;\\\">No, on the contrary it will increase 30% life of your engine. As the fuel is a gas, it mixes better with air than octane and you should find far less wear on the engine and certain components when using LPG due to the absence of acids and carbon deposits.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\"}', '{\"en\":\"LPG is the short name for Liquefied Petroleum Gas, this is a mixture of Propane and Butane extracted from Gas & Oil fields. LPG is a clean fuel that has a range of properties closest to Octane. LPG is the third most popular automotive fuel in the world.\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'benefits-of-lpg', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(42, '{\"en\":\"BANGLADESH LPG AUTOGAS STATION & CONVERSION WORKSHOP OWNER\'S ASSOCIATION\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; color: #444444; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Due to the depletion of natural gas reserves, there has been a gas crisis in the whole country. Considering these issues, the government has already encouraged the use of LPG autogas instead of petrol, octane and CNG in vehicles. More than 500+ LPG autogas stations have been installed and 300 autogas stations are under process to be constructed all over Bangladesh. With the promotion of LPG as an alternative-economical fuel, the consumption pressure on natural gas has started to decrease. On the other hand, the demand of LPG as an alternative-economical, safe and efficient vehicle fuel is increasing day by day with the promotion of LPG autogas stations in all areas where CNG filling stations are not available.<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; list-style: none; padding: 0px; color: #444444; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 10px 0px 0px 28px; position: relative;\\\">LPG Station and Conversion || LPG Autogas Station<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 10px 0px 0px 28px; position: relative;\\\">LPG Distribution || Domestic LPG System<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 10px 0px 0px 28px; position: relative;\\\">Fuel Station Management System || LPG Bottling Plant Equipments<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p class=\\\"font-italic\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #444444; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Our association has formed to bring all autogas stations under one unique platform and to expand, facilitate and secure this autogas business sector. We seek the cooperation of all concerned departments towards the development of the LPG autogas sector.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Government approved trade organization to manipulate the activities of all autogas stations and conversion workshops.\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'bangladesh-lpg-autogas-station-conversion-workshop-owner-s-association', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(43, '{\"en\":\"WHO WE ARE\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h2 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; color: #00523b;\\\">Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG) autogas is a rapidly growing industry in Bangladesh. Our association has formed to expand, facilitate and secure this autogas business sector so that new entrepreneurs can have a choice to invest in this sector.<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 15px 0px 30px; line-height: 24px; color: #444444; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\\\">Our main goal is to bring all autogas station and conversion workshop owners under one unique platform to manipulate their activities and promote LPG autogas as an environmentally friendly, alternative-economical, safe and efficient vehicle fuel so that the conversion of vehicles to LPG increases satisfactorily. We seek the attention of all concerned departments towards the development of the LPG autogas sector.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG) autogas is a rapidly growing industry in Bangladesh. Our association has formed to expand, facilitate and secure this autogas business sector so that new entrepreneurs can have a choice to invest in this sector.\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'who-we-are', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(44, '{\"en\":\"Poland Student Visa\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h3 class=\\\"title\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: montserratregular; line-height: 1.1; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 50px; padding-bottom: 10px; position: relative;\\\"><div class=\\\"single-item-text-info\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: montserratlight; vertical-align: baseline; margin-bottom: 18px; padding-top: 5px;\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\"><font color=\\\"#000000\\\"><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; vertical-align: baseline; margin-right: 11px;\\\">Spouse Visa<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: montserratregular; vertical-align: baseline; margin-right: 11px;\\\">Visit &amp; Business Visa<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; vertical-align: baseline; margin-right: 11px;\\\">Immigration Visa<\\/span><\\/font><\\/span><\\/div><div class=\\\"course-text-content student_visa\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: montserratlight; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 21px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\\"><font color=\\\"#000000\\\">Generally, students from EU\\/EEA countries don\'t need to apply for a student visa but they need to register their stay in Poland. You have to do this if you intend to stay for longer than three months. ... The process is cost-free and you will get a certificate of registration that proves your right to stay in Poland.<\\/font><\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\\"><font color=\\\"#000000\\\">If you are a citizen of an EU member state the only thing you need to have to enter Poland is a valid travel document or a document confirming identity and citizenship (i.e. your national ID). However, if you wish to travel abroad during your stay in Poland it is a good idea to have a passport with you,<\\/font><\\/span><\\/p><p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; text-align: justify;\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\\"><font color=\\\"#000000\\\"><br><\\/font><\\/span><\\/p><\\/div><\\/h3><h3 class=\\\"title\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: montserratregular; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(43, 40, 109); margin-top: 0px; font-size: 20px; padding-bottom: 10px; position: relative;\\\">Overview in Poland<\\/h3><h3 class=\\\"title\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: montserratregular; line-height: 1.1; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 50px; padding-bottom: 10px; position: relative;\\\"><div class=\\\"course-text-content student_visa\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: montserratlight; vertical-align: baseline;\\\"><p class=\\\"text-justify\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 7px; margin-left: 0px; color: rgb(85, 85, 85);\\\">You will enjoy high quality of teaching, but also have a chance to pursue your future career in EU. Polish schools compete with each other not only to provide a wide variety of high quality courses, but also offer attractive tuition fees in programs such as MBBS, engineering, international business, tourism, hospitality and other.<\\/p><\\/div><\\/h3>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Spouse Visa , Visit & Business Visa Immigration Visa\"}', '52611644840035.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'poland-student-visa', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(45, '{\"en\":\"HKBU Elizabeth Law Scholarship Fund For Mainland Students, Hong Kong 2022\"}', '{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"scholarship-item\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #3d4452; font-family: \'gotham book\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; outline: none !important;\\\">\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 8px; padding: 0px; font-family: gotham, sans-serif; font-weight: 600; line-height: 22px; color: #171a1f; font-size: 18px; position: relative; outline: none !important;\\\">Scholarship Description:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 22px; outline: none !important;\\\">HKBU Elizabeth Law Scholarship Fund for Mainland Students, Hong Kong 2022 is open for International Students . The scholarship allows Undergraduate level programm(s) in the field of Law taught at Hong Kong Baptist University(HKBU) . The deadline of the scholarship is Open.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"scholarship-item\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #3d4452; font-family: \'gotham book\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; outline: none !important;\\\">\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 8px; padding: 0px; font-family: gotham, sans-serif; font-weight: 600; line-height: 22px; color: #171a1f; font-size: 18px; position: relative; outline: none !important;\\\">Degree Level:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 22px; outline: none !important;\\\">HKBU Elizabeth Law Scholarship Fund for Mainland Students, Hong Kong 2022 is available to undertake Undergraduate level programs at Hong Kong Baptist University(HKBU).<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"scholarship-item\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #3d4452; font-family: \'gotham book\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; outline: none !important;\\\">\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 8px; padding: 0px; font-family: gotham, sans-serif; font-weight: 600; line-height: 22px; color: #171a1f; font-size: 18px; position: relative; outline: none !important;\\\">Available Subjects:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 22px; outline: none !important;\\\">Following subject are available to study under this scholarship program.<\\/p>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"scholarship-item\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; outline: none !important;\\\">\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 8px; padding: 0px; font-family: gotham, sans-serif; font-weight: 600; line-height: 22px; color: #171a1f; font-size: 18px; position: relative; outline: none !important;\\\">Scholarship Benefits:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 22px; user-select: auto; outline: none !important;\\\">The selected undergraduate students will be provided HK$195,000 towards their cost of study at Hong Kong Baptist University.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"scholarship-item\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; padding: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; outline: none !important;\\\">\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 8px; padding: 0px; font-family: gotham, sans-serif; font-weight: 600; line-height: 22px; color: #171a1f; font-size: 18px; position: relative; outline: none !important;\\\">Eligible Nationalities:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 22px; user-select: auto; outline: none !important;\\\">Mainland&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 22px; user-select: auto; outline: none !important;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #171a1f; font-family: gotham, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600;\\\">Eligibility Criteria:<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"scholarship-item\\\" style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 30px; padding: 0px; outline: none !important; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #3d4452; font-family: \'gotham book\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\\\">\\r\\n<table style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none !important; border-collapse: collapse; user-select: auto;\\\" border=\\\"0\\\" width=\\\"100%\\\" cellspacing=\\\"0\\\" cellpadding=\\\"0\\\" align=\\\"left\\\">\\r\\n<tbody style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none !important; user-select: auto;\\\">\\r\\n<tr style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none !important; user-select: auto;\\\">\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none !important; user-select: auto;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; outline: none !important; color: #3d4452; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 22px; user-select: auto;\\\">Students recruited from overseas to study the undergraduate degree program at the University.&nbsp;Renewable for normal duration of study subject to the student&rsquo;s achievement of good result.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none !important; user-select: auto;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody>\\r\\n<\\/table>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\"}', '{\"en\":\"HKBU Elizabeth Law Scholarship Fund for Mainland Students, Hong Kong 2022 is open for International Students . The scholarship allows Undergraduate level programm(s) in the field of Law taught at Hong Kong Baptist University(HKBU) . The deadline of the scholarship is Open.\"}', 'hkbu-elizabeth-law-scholarship-fund-for-mainland-students-hong-kong-2022_801644840487.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'hkbu-elizabeth-law-scholarship-fund-for-mainland-students-hong-kong-2022', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `excerpt`, `feature_img_name`, `feature_img_original_name`, `feature_img_mime`, `feature_img_ext`, `status`, `tags`, `read`, `headline`, `front_slider`, `highlight`, `publish_status`, `published_year`, `published_number`, `published_at`, `slug`, `addedby_id`, `writer_id`, `editedby_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(46, '{\"en\":\"Japan offers Bangladeshi students the opportunity\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.1165px;\\\">The Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology (Monbukagakusho\\/MEXT) of the Government of Japan offers scholarships to foreign students who wish to study at Japanese universities and schools. Only&nbsp;Bangladeshi&nbsp;citizens can apply for these programs.&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">As per Embassy recommendation,<\\/span><span style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.1165px;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">all applications should be submitted to the Ministry of Education<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"main-section section\\\" style=\\\"margin: 30px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 1.6; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"section-block image-section-top\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; display: flex; flex-flow: column wrap;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 10px; text-size-adjust: 100%; width: 1243.33px; box-sizing: border-box; min-height: 0%;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"any-area\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Before beginning the application process, please review&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/itpr_en\\/education.html\\\">our webpage<\\/a>&nbsp; for more information on studying in Japan, information on Japanese universities, and MEXT Scholarship Alumni.<br \\/><br \\/>Categories of the MEXT scholarship (Embassy recommendation):<br \\/>-Research Students (Application now closed)<br \\/>-Undergraduate Students (Appliction now closed)<br \\/>-Specialized Training School Students (Application now closed)<br \\/>-College of Technology Students (Application now closed)<br \\/>-Japanese Studies Students (<span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_red\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #ff0000;\\\">Appliction is now open<\\/span>)<br \\/>-Teachers Training Students (<span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_red\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #ff0000;\\\">Application is&nbsp;now open<\\/span>)<br \\/><br \\/>(Please refer to the below sections for the details)<br \\/>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div id=\\\"section2\\\" class=\\\"main-section section\\\" style=\\\"margin: 30px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 1.6; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">\\r\\n<h2 class=\\\"title2\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px; background: linear-gradient(#ffffff, #f0f0f0 30%, #dbdbdb); border: 1px solid #bfbfbf; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 9px 10px 8px; text-size-adjust: 100%; display: block; border-left: 5px solid #6b6bcf;\\\">Research Students<\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"section-block image-section-top\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; display: flex; flex-flow: column wrap;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 10px; text-size-adjust: 100%; width: 1243.33px; box-sizing: border-box; min-height: 0%;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"any-area\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: blue;\\\"><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">Application for the MEXT 2022 Research Students Scholarship (Embassy recommendation) is<span style=\\\"color: #000000; font-family: Calibri;\\\">&nbsp;<span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">already CLOSED<\\/span><\\/span>.<\\/span><br \\/>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Duration:&nbsp;Approx. 2 years or more depending on the program (please refer to the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/100193455.pdf\\\"><u>Application Guidelines<\\/u>&nbsp;<\\/a>for more details)<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Outline of Eligibility:&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Degree:<\\/em>&nbsp;Bachelor\'s degree or higher \\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Age:<\\/em>&nbsp;born on or after April 2, 1987 (for the 2022 recruitment) \\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Study Area:<\\/em>&nbsp;the same field that the applicant has studied, or a related field \\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Citizenship:<\\/em>&nbsp;Bangladeshi<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Departure Date:&nbsp;April or October 2022<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Placement at University:&nbsp;Designated by MEXT, based on your admission or a letter of provisional acceptance you obtain from Japanese universities.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Selection Process:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ol style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px 20px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; list-style-position: inside; list-style-image: initial; line-height: 1.6;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Application Submission:&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.shed.gov.bd\\/site\\/view\\/scholarship\\/%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9E%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">To the Ministry of Education, Bangladesh<\\/span><\\/a><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Documents Review<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Examination (Japanese and English)&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">1st screening notification&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Obtain admissions or letters of provisional acceptance<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">2nd screening notification&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Acceptance notification&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div id=\\\"section3\\\" class=\\\"main-section section\\\" style=\\\"margin: 30px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 1.6; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"section-block image-section-top\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; display: flex; flex-flow: column wrap;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 10px; text-size-adjust: 100%; width: 1243.33px; box-sizing: border-box; min-height: 0%;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"any-area\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: blue;\\\"><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-weight: bold;\\\">Undergraduate Students<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: blue;\\\"><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">Application for the MEXT 2022 Undergraduate Students Scholarship&nbsp;is&nbsp;<\\/span><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_blue\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">already CLOSED<\\/span><\\/span><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Duration:&nbsp;Approx. 4-6 years depending on the program (please refer to the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/100193456.pdf\\\"><u>Application Guidelines<\\/u>&nbsp;<\\/a>for more details)<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Outline of Eligibility:&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Education<\\/em>: High school diploma or higher \\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Age<\\/em>: 17-25 \\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Citizenship<\\/em>: Bangladeshi<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Departure Date:&nbsp;April&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Placement at University:&nbsp;Designated by MEXT, based on your fields and subjects choices.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Selection Process:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ol style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px 20px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; list-style-position: inside; list-style-image: initial; line-height: 1.6;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Application Submission:&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.shed.gov.bd\\/site\\/view\\/scholarship\\/%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9E%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">To the Ministry of Education, Bangladesh<\\/span><\\/a><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Documents Review<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Examination (Japanese, English, Mathematics and Science*)&nbsp;<br \\/>*Only for applicants who choose Natural Science field<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">1st screening notification<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Acceptance notification&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div id=\\\"section4\\\" class=\\\"main-section section\\\" style=\\\"margin: 30px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 1.6; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"section-block image-section-top\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; display: flex; flex-flow: column wrap;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 10px; text-size-adjust: 100%; width: 1243.33px; box-sizing: border-box; min-height: 0%;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"any-area\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: blue;\\\"><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-weight: bold;\\\">Specialized Training College Students<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: blue;\\\"><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">Application for the MEXT 2022 Specialized Training College&nbsp;Students Scholarship&nbsp;is&nbsp;<\\/span><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_blue\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">already CLOSED<\\/span><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">.<\\/span><br \\/>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Duration:&nbsp;3 years (including one-year preparatory&nbsp;education in the Japanese language and other subjecgts due to be provided upon arrival in Japan. Please refer to the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/100193458.pdf\\\"><u>Application Guidelines<\\/u><\\/a>&nbsp;for more details.<br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Fields of Study:<\\/span><br \\/>A) Technology<br \\/>B)&nbsp;Personal Care and Nutrition<br \\/>C)&nbsp;Education and Welfare<br \\/>D)&nbsp;Business<br \\/>E) Fashion and Home Economics<br \\/>F)&nbsp;Culture and Feneral Education<br \\/>Details:&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/000474684.pdf\\\">Fields of Study for the Training College Students Scholarship<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Outline of Eligibility:&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Education<\\/em>: Those who are enrolled in a postsecondary course at a specialized training college, or who are receiving preparatory education in Japanese language and other subjects prior to placement at the specialized training college. \\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Age<\\/em>: 17-25 \\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Citizenship<\\/em>: Bangladeshi<br \\/>Please refer to the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/000474697.pdf\\\">Application Guideline for Specialized Training College Students Scholarship&nbsp;<\\/a>for the details.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Departure Date:&nbsp;April&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Application Deadline:&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Selection Process:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ol style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px 20px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; list-style-position: inside; list-style-image: initial; line-height: 1.6;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Application Submission:&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.shed.gov.bd\\/site\\/view\\/scholarship\\/%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9E%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">To the Ministry of Education, Bangladesh<\\/span><\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Documents Review<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Examination (Japanese, English, Mathematics and Chemistry or\\/and Physics)&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">1st screening notification<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Acceptance notification&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div id=\\\"section5\\\" class=\\\"main-section section\\\" style=\\\"margin: 30px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%; line-height: 1.6; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"section-block image-section-top\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; display: flex; flex-flow: column wrap;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 10px; text-size-adjust: 100%; width: 1243.33px; box-sizing: border-box; min-height: 0%;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"any-area\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-weight: bold;\\\">College of Technology Students<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Application for the MEXT 2022 College of Technology&nbsp;Students Scholarship&nbsp;is&nbsp;<span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_blue\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #0000ff;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">already CLOSED<\\/span><\\/span>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Duration:&nbsp;4 years (one-year preparatory Japanese language course,&nbsp;and then enrolled into the third year of the course at the college of technology and receive specialized education for three years). Please refer to the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/100193459.pdf\\\"><u>Application Guidelines<\\/u>&nbsp;<\\/a>for more details.<br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Fields of Study:<\\/span><br \\/>A) Mechanical Engineering<br \\/>B) Electrical and Electronic Engineering<br \\/>C) Information, Communication and Netword Engineering<br \\/>D) Materials Engineering<br \\/>E) Architecture<br \\/>F) Civil Engineering<br \\/>G) Maritime Engineering<br \\/>H) Other Fields<br \\/>Details:&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/000474695.pdf\\\">Field of Study for the College of Technology Students Scholarship<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Outline of Eligibility:&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Education<\\/em>: Applicants must be eligible for transferring&nbsp;admission to a third-year course at a collge of technology at the time of application.\\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Age<\\/em>: 17-25 \\/&nbsp;<em style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Citizenship<\\/em>: Bangladeshi<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Departure Date:&nbsp;April&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Selection Process:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ol style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px 20px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; list-style-position: inside; list-style-image: initial; line-height: 1.6;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Application Submission:&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.shed.gov.bd\\/site\\/view\\/scholarship\\/%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9E%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BF\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">To the Ministry of Education, Bangladesh<\\/span><\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Documents Review<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Examination (Japanese, English, Mathematics and Chemistry or\\/and Physics)&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">1st screening notification<\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Acceptance notification&nbsp;<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n<div id=\\\"section2\\\" class=\\\"section\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text_area\\\" style=\\\"margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; text-size-adjust: 100%; zoom: 1; width: auto;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px 0px 20px; text-size-adjust: 100%; overflow: hidden; min-height: 0%;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: blue;\\\"><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-weight: bold;\\\">Japanese Studies Students<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: blue;\\\"><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">Application for the MEXT 2022 Japanese Studies Students Scholarship&nbsp;is<\\/span><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_red\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #ff0000;\\\">&nbsp;now OPEN<\\/span><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">.<\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Duration<\\/span>: 1 year<\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">Departure Date<\\/span><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">: September-October<\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Outline of Eligibility<\\/span>:<\\/span><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1. Bangladeshi citizen<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.11px;\\\" \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2. Born between April 2, 1992 and April 1, 2004<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.11px;\\\" \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3. Currently enrolled as an undergraduate student and majoring in fields related to Japanese language and\\/or Japanese culture.<br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Application<\\/span>:<br \\/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1. Read<\\/span><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/span><a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/000546503.pdf\\\">Application Guideline<\\/a><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2. Visit&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.shed.gov.bd\\/site\\/view\\/scholarship\\/Scholarship-Notification\\\">Ministry of Education website<\\/a><br \\/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 3. Submit Application form to Ministry of Education<\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Exam and Interview Date<\\/span>: TBC (2022 February)<br \\/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; *We will contact the&nbsp;candidate who qualified the document screening only.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2 style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px; background-image: linear-gradient(#ffffff, #f0f0f0 30%, #dbdbdb); background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border: 1px solid #bfbfbf; font-size: 15.1165px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #222222;\\\">Teachers Training Students<\\/h2>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text_area\\\" style=\\\"margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; font-size: 16px; text-size-adjust: 100%; zoom: 1; width: auto; color: #222222;\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"text\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px 0px 20px; text-size-adjust: 100%; overflow: hidden; min-height: 0%;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: blue;\\\"><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_firebrick\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #b22222;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">Application for the MEXT 2022 Teachers Training Students Scholarship<\\/span><\\/span><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_red\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #ff0000;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\">&nbsp;is<\\/span>&nbsp;<span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">now OPEN.<\\/span><\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Duration<\\/span>: 1.5 years<\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">Departure Date<\\/span><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">:&nbsp; September-October<\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><span class=\\\"aly_tx_f_black\\\" style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000000;\\\"><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Outline of Eligibility<\\/span>:<br \\/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1. Bangladeshi citizen<\\/span><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2. Born on or after April 2, 1987<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.11px;\\\" \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3. At least (5) five years of teaching experience in primary or secondary schools as of October 1, 2022.<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.11px;\\\" \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4. Currently employed as a teacher in an elementary or secondary school<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.11px;\\\" \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;5. Interested in and willing to learn about Japanese culture<br \\/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;6. Upon completion MEXT Teacher\'s Training Scholarship awardees are required to return to Bangladesh and resume their roles in their organizations as teachers\\/ trainers.&nbsp;<br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Application<\\/span>:<br \\/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1. Read&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.bd.emb-japan.go.jp\\/files\\/000546987.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\">Application Guideline<\\/a><br \\/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2. Visit&nbsp;<a style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #000066; background-color: transparent;\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.shed.gov.bd\\/site\\/view\\/scholarship\\/Scholarship-Notification\\\">Ministry of Education website<\\/a><\\/span><br style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.11px;\\\" \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;3. Submit Application form to Ministry of Education<br \\/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">Exam and Interview Date<\\/span><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">: TBC (2022 February)<\\/span><br style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.11px;\\\" \\/><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; *We will contact the<\\/span><span style=\\\"color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;; font-size: 15.11px;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 15.11px; text-size-adjust: 100%; color: #333333; font-family: &quot;&quot;;\\\">candidate who qualified the document screening only.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\"}', '{\"en\":\"The Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology (Monbukagakusho\\/MEXT) of the Government of Japan offers scholarships to foreign students who wish to study at Japanese universities and schools. Only Bangladeshi citizens can apply for these programs. As per Embassy recommendation, all applications should be submitted to the Ministry of Education\"}', 'japan-offers-bangladeshi-students-the-opportunity_491644840920.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'japan-offers-bangladeshi-students-the-opportunity', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(47, '{\"en\":\"IOT (Internet of things)\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The&nbsp;<strong>Internet of things<\\/strong>&nbsp;(<strong>IoT<\\/strong>) describes physical objects (or groups of such objects) that are embedded with&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Sensor\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Sensor\\\">sensors<\\/a>, processing ability,&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Software\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software\\\">software<\\/a>, and other technologies that connect and exchange data with other devices and systems over the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Internet\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Internet\\\">Internet<\\/a>&nbsp;or other communications networks.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The field has evolved due to the convergence of multiple&nbsp;<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Technologies\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Technologies\\\">technologies<\\/a>, including&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Ubiquitous computing\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Ubiquitous_computing\\\">ubiquitous computing<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Commodity\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Commodity\\\">commodity<\\/a>&nbsp;<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Sensors\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Sensors\\\">sensors<\\/a>, increasingly powerful&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Embedded system\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Embedded_system\\\">embedded systems<\\/a>, and&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Machine learning\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Machine_learning\\\">machine learning<\\/a>. Traditional fields of&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Embedded system\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Embedded_system\\\">embedded systems<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Wireless sensor network\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wireless_sensor_network\\\">wireless sensor networks<\\/a>, control systems,&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Automation\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Automation\\\">automation<\\/a>&nbsp;(including&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Home automation\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Home_automation\\\">home<\\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Building automation\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Building_automation\\\">building automation<\\/a>), independently and collectively enable the Internet of things. In the consumer market, IoT technology is most synonymous with products pertaining to the concept of the \\\"<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Smart home technology\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Smart_home_technology\\\">smart home<\\/a>\\\", including devices and&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Home appliance\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Home_appliance\\\">appliances<\\/a>&nbsp;(such as lighting fixtures,&nbsp;<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Thermostats\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Thermostats\\\">thermostats<\\/a>, home&nbsp;<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Security systems\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Security_systems\\\">security systems<\\/a>&nbsp;and cameras, and other home appliances) that support one or more common ecosystems, and can be controlled via devices associated with that ecosystem, such as&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Smartphone\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Smartphone\\\">smartphones<\\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Smart speaker\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Smart_speaker\\\">smart speakers<\\/a>. The IoT can also be used in&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Health system\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Health_system\\\">healthcare systems<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">There are a number of concerns about the risks in the growth of IoT technologies and products, especially in the areas of&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Digital privacy\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Digital_privacy\\\">privacy<\\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Digital security\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Digital_security\\\">security<\\/a>, and consequently, industry and governmental moves to address these concerns have begun, including the development of international and local standards, guidelines, and regulatory frameworks.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-6\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a style=\\\"color: #0645ad; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Internet_of_things#cite_note-6\\\">[6]<\\/a><\\/sup><\\/p>\\r\\n<div id=\\\"3620C28B_F487_0259_4E8B_788CDB50F172\\\"><\\/div>\"}', '{\"en\":\"The Internet of things (IoT) describes physical objects (or groups of such objects) that are embedded with sensors, processing ability, software, and other technologies that connect and exchange data with other devices and systems over the Internet or other communications networks.\"}', '60291644905586.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'iot-internet-of-things', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `excerpt`, `feature_img_name`, `feature_img_original_name`, `feature_img_mime`, `feature_img_ext`, `status`, `tags`, `read`, `headline`, `front_slider`, `highlight`, `publish_status`, `published_year`, `published_number`, `published_at`, `slug`, `addedby_id`, `writer_id`, `editedby_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(48, '{\"en\":\"History about IOT\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The main concept of a network of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Smart_device\\\" title=\\\"Smart device\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">smart devices<\\/a>&nbsp;was discussed as early as 1982, with a modified&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Coca-Cola\\\" title=\\\"Coca-Cola\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Coca-Cola<\\/a>&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Vending_machine\\\" title=\\\"Vending machine\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">vending machine<\\/a>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Carnegie_Mellon_University\\\" title=\\\"Carnegie Mellon University\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Carnegie Mellon University<\\/a>&nbsp;becoming the first&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/ARPANET\\\" title=\\\"ARPANET\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">ARPANET<\\/a>-connected appliance,&nbsp;able to report its inventory and whether newly loaded drinks were cold or not.&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Mark_Weiser\\\" title=\\\"Mark Weiser\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Mark Weiser<\\/a>\'s 1991 paper on&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Ubiquitous_computing\\\" title=\\\"Ubiquitous computing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">ubiquitous computing<\\/a>, \\\"The Computer of the 21st Century\\\", as well as academic venues such as UbiComp and PerCom produced the contemporary vision of the IoT. In 1994, Reza Raji described the concept in&nbsp;<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/IEEE_Spectrum\\\" title=\\\"IEEE Spectrum\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">IEEE Spectrum<\\/a><\\/i>&nbsp;as \\\"[moving] small packets of data to a large set of nodes, so as to integrate and automate everything from home appliances to entire factories\\\".&nbsp;Between 1993 and 1997, several companies proposed solutions like&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Microsoft\\\" title=\\\"Microsoft\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Microsoft<\\/a>\'s&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/At_Work\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"At Work\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">at Work<\\/a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Novell\\\" title=\\\"Novell\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Novell<\\/a>\'s&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Novell_Embedded_Systems_Technology\\\" title=\\\"Novell Embedded Systems Technology\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">NEST<\\/a>. The field gained momentum when&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Bill_Joy\\\" title=\\\"Bill Joy\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Bill Joy<\\/a>&nbsp;envisioned&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Device-to-device\\\" title=\\\"Device-to-device\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">device-to-device<\\/a>&nbsp;communication as a part of his \\\"Six Webs\\\" framework, presented at the World Economic Forum at Davos in 1999.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The concept of the \\\"Internet of things\\\" and the term itself, first appeared in a speech by Peter T. Lewis, to the Congressional Black Caucus Foundation 15th Annual Legislative Weekend in Washington, D.C, published in September 1985.&nbsp;According to Lewis, \\\"The Internet of Things, or IoT, is the integration of people, processes and technology with connectable devices and sensors to enable remote monitoring, status, manipulation and evaluation of trends of such devices.\\\"<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The term \\\"Internet of things\\\" was coined independently by&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Kevin_Ashton\\\" title=\\\"Kevin Ashton\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Kevin Ashton<\\/a>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Procter_%26_Gamble\\\" title=\\\"Procter &amp; Gamble\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Procter &amp; Gamble<\\/a>, later&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\\\" title=\\\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">MIT<\\/a>\'s&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Auto-ID_Labs\\\" title=\\\"Auto-ID Labs\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Auto-ID Center<\\/a>, in 1999, though he prefers the phrase \\\"Internet&nbsp;<i>for<\\/i>&nbsp;things\\\".&nbsp;At that point, he viewed&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Radio-frequency_identification\\\" title=\\\"Radio-frequency identification\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">radio-frequency identification<\\/a>&nbsp;(RFID) as essential to the Internet of things,&nbsp;which would allow computers to manage all individual things. The main theme of the Internet of things is to embed short-range mobile transceivers in various gadgets and daily necessities to enable new forms of communication between people and things, and between things themselves.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Defining the Internet of things as \\\"simply the point in time when more \'things or objects\' were connected to the Internet than people\\\",&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Cisco_Systems\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Cisco Systems\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Cisco Systems<\\/a>&nbsp;estimated that the IoT was \\\"born\\\" between 2008 and 2009, with the things\\/people ratio growing from 0.08 in 2003 to 1.84 in 2010.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"The main concept of a network of smart devices was discussed as early as 1982, with a modified Coca-Cola vending machine at Carnegie Mellon University becoming the first ARPANET-connected appliance, able to report its inventory and whether newly loaded drinks were cold or not. Mark Weiser\'s 1991 paper on ubiquitous computing, \\\"The Computer of the 21st Century\\\", as well as academic venues such as UbiComp and PerCom produced the contemporary vision of the IoT. In 1994, Reza Raji described the concept in IEEE Spectrum as \\\"[moving] small packets of data to a large set of nodes, so as to integrate and automate everything from home appliances to entire factories\\\". Between 1993 and 1997, several companies proposed solutions like Microsoft\'s at Work or Novell\'s NEST. The field gained momentum when Bill Joy envisioned device-to-device communication as a part of his \\\"Six Webs\\\" framework, presented at the World Economic Forum at Davos in 1999.\"}', '65121644905835.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'history-about-iot', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(49, '{\"en\":\"Industrial applications of IOT\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h3 style=\\\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span id=\\\"Industrial_applications\\\" class=\\\"mw-headline\\\">Industrial applications<\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\\\" style=\\\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\" role=\\\"note\\\">Main article:&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Industrial internet of things\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Industrial_internet_of_things\\\">Industrial internet of things<\\/a><\\/div>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">Also known as IIoT, industrial IoT devices acquire and analyze data from connected equipment, operational technology (OT), locations, and people. Combined with operational technology (OT) monitoring devices, IIoT helps regulate and monitor industrial systems. Also, the same implementation can be carried out for automated record updates of asset placement in industrial storage units as the size of the assets can vary from a small screw to the whole motor spare part, and misplacement of such assets can cause a percentile loss of manpower time and money.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h4 style=\\\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span id=\\\"Manufacturing\\\" class=\\\"mw-headline\\\"><span id=\\\"IIoT\\\" class=\\\"anchor\\\"><\\/span>Manufacturing<\\/span><\\/h4>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">The IoT can connect various manufacturing devices equipped with sensing, identification, processing, communication, actuation, and networking capabilities.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-IoT-Manufacturing_Survey_62-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup>&nbsp;Network control and management of&nbsp;<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Reconfigurable Manufacturing System\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Reconfigurable_Manufacturing_System\\\">manufacturing equipment<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Asset management\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Asset_management\\\">asset<\\/a>&nbsp;and situation management, or manufacturing&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Process control\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Process_control\\\">process control<\\/a>&nbsp;allow IoT to be used for industrial applications and smart manufacturing.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-Butler-M2M_63-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Internet_of_things#cite_note-Butler-M2M-63\\\">[63]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;IoT intelligent systems enable rapid manufacturing and optimization of new products and rapid response to product demands.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-CoMAN_47-3\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Digital control\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Digital_control\\\">Digital control systems<\\/a>&nbsp;to automate process controls, operator tools and service information systems to optimize plant safety and security are within the purview of the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Industrial internet of things\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Industrial_internet_of_things\\\">IoT<\\/a>. <sup id=\\\"cite_ref-IoT-Survey_64-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup>IoT can also be applied to asset management via&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Predictive maintenance\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Predictive_maintenance\\\">predictive maintenance<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Statistical model\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Statistical_model\\\">statistical evaluation<\\/a>, and measurements to maximize reliability.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-Future-IoT_65-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup>&nbsp;Industrial management systems can be integrated with&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Smart grid\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Smart_grid\\\">smart grids<\\/a>, enabling energy optimization. Measurements, automated controls, plant optimization, health and safety management, and other functions are provided by networked sensors.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-CoMAN_47-4\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">In addition to general manufacturing, IoT is also used for processes in the industrialization of construction.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-66\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/p>\\r\\n<h4 style=\\\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span id=\\\"Agriculture\\\" class=\\\"mw-headline\\\">Agriculture<\\/span><\\/h4>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">There are numerous IoT applications in farming<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-MeolaWhy16_67-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup>&nbsp;such as collecting data on temperature, rainfall, humidity, wind speed, pest infestation, and soil content. This data can be used to automate farming techniques, make informed decisions to improve quality and quantity, minimize risk and waste, and reduce the effort required to manage crops. For example, farmers can now monitor soil temperature and moisture from afar and even apply IoT-acquired data to precision fertilization programs.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-ZhangPrecision15_68-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup>&nbsp;The overall goal is that data from sensors, coupled with the farmer\'s knowledge and intuition about his or her farm, can help increase farm productivity, and also help reduce costs.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">In August 2018,&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Toyota Tsusho\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Toyota_Tsusho\\\">Toyota Tsusho<\\/a>&nbsp;began a partnership with&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Microsoft\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Microsoft\\\">Microsoft<\\/a>&nbsp;to create&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Fish farming\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Fish_farming\\\">fish farming<\\/a>&nbsp;tools using the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Microsoft Azure\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Microsoft_Azure\\\">Microsoft Azure<\\/a>&nbsp;application suite for IoT technologies related to water management. Developed in part by researchers from&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Kindai University\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Kindai_University\\\">Kindai University<\\/a>, the water pump mechanisms use&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Artificial intelligence\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Artificial_intelligence\\\">artificial intelligence<\\/a>&nbsp;to count the number of fish on a&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Conveyor belt\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Conveyor_belt\\\">conveyor belt<\\/a>, analyze the number of fish, and deduce the effectiveness of water flow from the data the fish provide.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-69\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup>&nbsp;The FarmBeats project<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-70\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup>&nbsp;from Microsoft Research that uses TV white space to connect farms is also a part of the Azure Marketplace now.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-71\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/p>\\r\\n<h4 style=\\\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span id=\\\"Maritime\\\" class=\\\"mw-headline\\\">Maritime<\\/span><\\/h4>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">IoT devices are in use monitoring the environments and systems of boats and yachts.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-72\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup>&nbsp;Many pleasure boats are left unattended for days in summer, and months in winter so such devices provide valuable early alerts of boat flooding, fire, and deep discharge of batteries. The use of global internet data networks such as&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Sigfox\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Sigfox\\\">Sigfox<\\/a>, combined with long-life batteries, and microelectronics allows the engine rooms, bilge, and batteries to be constantly monitored and reported to connected Android &amp; Apple applications for example.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"industrial IoT devices acquire and analyze data from connected equipment, operational technology (OT), locations, and people. Combined with operational technology (OT) monitoring devices, IIoT helps regulate and monitor industrial systems. Also, the same implementation can be carried out for automated record updates of asset placement in industrial storage units as the size of the assets can vary from a small screw to the whole motor spare part, and misplacement of such assets can cause a percentile loss of manpower time and money.\"}', '12151644905986.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'industrial-applications-of-iot', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(50, '{\"en\":\"Infrastructure applications of IOT\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Monitoring and controlling operations of sustainable urban and rural infrastructures like bridges, railway tracks and on- and offshore wind farms is a key application of the IoT.&nbsp;The IoT infrastructure can be used for monitoring any events or changes in structural conditions that can compromise safety and increase risk. The IoT can benefit the construction industry by cost-saving, time reduction, better quality workday, paperless workflow and increase in productivity. It can help in taking faster decisions and save money with Real-Time Data Analytics. It can also be used for scheduling repair and maintenance activities in an efficient manner, by coordinating tasks between different service providers and users of these facilities.&nbsp;IoT devices can also be used to control critical infrastructure like bridges to provide access to ships. Usage of IoT devices for monitoring and operating infrastructure is likely to improve incident management and emergency response coordination,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Quality_of_service\\\" title=\\\"Quality of service\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">quality of service<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Uptime\\\" title=\\\"Uptime\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">up-times<\\/a>&nbsp;and reduce costs of operation in all infrastructure related areas.&nbsp;Even areas such as waste management can benefit&nbsp;from&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Automation\\\" title=\\\"Automation\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">automation<\\/a>&nbsp;and optimization that could be brought in by the IoT.<\\/p><h4 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-headline\\\" id=\\\"Metropolitan_scale_deployments\\\">Metropolitan scale deployments<\\/span><\\/h4><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">There are several planned or ongoing large-scale deployments of the IoT, to enable better management of cities and systems. For example,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Songdo_International_Business_District\\\" title=\\\"Songdo International Business District\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Songdo<\\/a>, South Korea, the first of its kind fully equipped and wired&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Smart_city\\\" title=\\\"Smart city\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">smart city<\\/a>, is gradually being built, with approximately 70 per cent of the business district completed as of June&nbsp;2018. Much of the city is planned to be wired and automated, with little or no human intervention.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Another application is currently undergoing a project in&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Santander,_Spain\\\" title=\\\"Santander, Spain\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Santander<\\/a>, Spain. For this deployment, two approaches have been adopted. This city of 180,000 inhabitants has already seen 18,000 downloads of its city smartphone app. The app is connected to 10,000 sensors that enable services like parking search, environmental monitoring, digital city agenda, and more. City context information is used in this deployment so as to benefit merchants through a spark deals mechanism based on city behaviour that aims at maximizing the impact of each notification.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Other examples of large-scale deployments underway include the Sino-Singapore Guangzhou Knowledge City; work on improving air and water quality, reducing noise pollution, and increasing transportation efficiency in San Jose, California;&nbsp;and smart traffic management in western Singapore.&nbsp;Using its RPMA (Random Phase Multiple Access) technologies, San Diego-based&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Ingenu\\\" title=\\\"Ingenu\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Ingenu<\\/a>&nbsp;has built a nationwide public network&nbsp;for low-bandwidth data transmissions using the same unlicensed 2.4 gigahertz spectrum as Wi-Fi. Ingenu\'s \\\"Machine Network\\\" covers more than a third of the US population across 35 major cities including San Diego and Dallas.&nbsp;A French company,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Sigfox\\\" title=\\\"Sigfox\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Sigfox<\\/a>, commenced building an&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Ultra_Narrowband\\\" title=\\\"Ultra Narrowband\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Ultra Narrowband<\\/a>&nbsp;wireless data network in the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/San_Francisco_Bay_Area\\\" title=\\\"San Francisco Bay Area\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">San Francisco Bay Area<\\/a>&nbsp;in 2014, the first business to achieve such a deployment in the U.S.&nbsp;It subsequently announced it would set up a total of 4000&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Base_station\\\" title=\\\"Base station\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">base stations<\\/a>&nbsp;to cover a total of 30 cities in the U.S. by the end of 2016, making it the largest IoT network coverage provider in the country thus far.&nbsp;Cisco also participates in smart cities projects. Cisco has started deploying technologies for Smart Wi-Fi, Smart Safety &amp; Security, Smart Lighting, Smart Parking, Smart Transports, Smart Bus Stops, Smart Kiosks, Remote Expert for Government Services (REGS) and Smart Education in the five km area in the city of Vijaywada.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Another example of a large deployment is the one completed by New York Waterways in New York City to connect all the city\'s vessels and be able to monitor them live 24\\/7. The network was designed and engineered by&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Fluidmesh\\\" title=\\\"Fluidmesh\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Fluidmesh<\\/a>&nbsp;Networks, a Chicago-based company developing wireless networks for critical applications. The NYWW network is currently providing coverage on the Hudson River, East River, and Upper New York Bay. With the wireless network in place, NY Waterway is able to take control of its fleet and passengers in a way that was not previously possible. New applications can include security, energy and fleet management, digital signage, public Wi-Fi, paperless ticketing and others.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-87\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Internet_of_things#cite_note-87\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">[87]<\\/a><\\/sup><\\/p><h4 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-headline\\\" id=\\\"Energy_management\\\">Energy management<\\/span><\\/h4><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Significant numbers of energy-consuming devices (e.g. lamps, household appliances, motors, pumps, etc.) already integrate Internet connectivity, which can allow them to communicate with utilities not only to balance&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Electricity_generation\\\" title=\\\"Electricity generation\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">power generation<\\/a>&nbsp;but also helps optimize the energy consumption as a whole.&nbsp;These devices allow for remote control by users, or central management via a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Cloud_computing\\\" title=\\\"Cloud computing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">cloud<\\/a>-based interface, and enable functions like scheduling (e.g., remotely powering on or off heating systems, controlling ovens, changing lighting conditions etc.).&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Smart_grid\\\" title=\\\"Smart grid\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">smart grid<\\/a>&nbsp;is a utility-side IoT application; systems gather and act on energy and power-related information to improve the efficiency of the production and distribution of electricity.&nbsp;Using&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Smart_meter\\\" title=\\\"Smart meter\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">advanced metering infrastructure (AMI)<\\/a>&nbsp;Internet-connected devices, electric utilities not only collect data from end-users but also manage distribution automation devices like transformers.<\\/p><h4 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-headline\\\" id=\\\"Environmental_monitoring\\\">Environmental monitoring<\\/span><\\/h4><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Environmental_monitoring\\\" title=\\\"Environmental monitoring\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Environmental monitoring<\\/a>&nbsp;applications of the IoT typically use sensors to assist in environmental protection&nbsp;by monitoring&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Air_quality\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Air quality\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">air<\\/a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Water_quality\\\" title=\\\"Water quality\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">water quality<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Air_pollution\\\" title=\\\"Air pollution\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">atmospheric<\\/a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Soil_pollution\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Soil pollution\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">soil conditions<\\/a>,&nbsp;and can even include areas like monitoring the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Animal_migration_tracking\\\" title=\\\"Animal migration tracking\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">movements of wildlife<\\/a>&nbsp;and their&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Habitat\\\" title=\\\"Habitat\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">habitats<\\/a>. The development of resource-constrained devices connected to the Internet also means that other applications like&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Earthquake_warning_system\\\" title=\\\"Earthquake warning system\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">earthquake<\\/a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Tsunami_warning_system\\\" title=\\\"Tsunami warning system\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">tsunami early-warning systems<\\/a>&nbsp;can also be used by emergency services to provide more effective aid. IoT devices in this application typically span a large geographic area and can also be mobile.&nbsp;It has been argued that the standardization that IoT brings to wireless sensing will revolutionize this area.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-93\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Internet_of_things#cite_note-93\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">[93]<\\/a><\\/sup><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\"><b>Living Lab<\\/b><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Another example of integrating the IoT is Living Lab which integrates and combines research and innovation processes, establishing within a public-private-people-partnership.&nbsp;There are currently 320 Living Labs that use the IoT to collaborate and share knowledge between stakeholders to co-create innovative and technological products. For companies to implement and develop&nbsp;<a rel=\\\"nofollow\\\" class=\\\"external text\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/thinkpalm.com\\/technologies\\/internet-of-things\\/\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(51, 102, 187); background-image: url(&quot;\\/w\\/skins\\/Vector\\/resources\\/common\\/images\\/external-link-ltr-icon.svg?48e54&quot;); background-position: right center; background-size: initial; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; padding-right: 13px;\\\">IoT services<\\/a>&nbsp;for smart cities, they need to have incentives. The governments play key roles in smart city projects as changes in policies will help cities to implement the IoT which provides effectiveness, efficiency, and accuracy of the resources that are being used. For instance, the government provides tax incentives and cheap rent, improves public transport, and offers an environment where start-up companies, creative industries, and multinationals may co-create, share a common infrastructure and labour markets, and take advantage of locally embedded technologies, production process, and transaction costs.&nbsp;The relationship between the technology developers and governments who manage the city\'s assets is key to providing open access to resources to users in an efficient way.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Monitoring and controlling operations of sustainable urban and rural infrastructures like bridges, railway tracks and on- and offshore wind farms is a key application of the IoT. The IoT infrastructure can be used for monitoring any events or changes in structural conditions that can compromise safety and increase risk. The IoT can benefit the construction industry by cost-saving, time reduction, better quality workday, paperless workflow and increase in productivity. It can help in taking faster decisions and save money with Real-Time Data Analytics. It can also be used for scheduling repair and maintenance activities in an efficient manner, by coordinating tasks between different service providers and users of these facilities. IoT devices can also be used to control critical infrastructure like bridges to provide access to ships. Usage of IoT devices for monitoring and operating infrastructure is likely to improve incident management and emergency response coordination, quality of service, up-times and reduce costs of operation in all infrastructure related areas. Even areas such as waste management can benefit from automation and optimization that could be brought in by the IoT.\"}', '64981644906490.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'infrastructure-applications-of-iot', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(51, '{\"en\":\"IOT Military applications\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Internet_of_Military_Things\\\" title=\\\"Internet of Military Things\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Internet of Military Things (IoMT)<\\/a>&nbsp;is the application of IoT technologies in the military domain for the purposes of reconnaissance, surveillance, and other combat-related objectives. It is heavily influenced by the future prospects of warfare in an urban environment and involves the use of sensors, munitions, vehicles, robots, human-wearable biometrics, and other smart technology that is relevant on the battlefield.<\\/p><h4 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-headline\\\" id=\\\"Internet_of_Battlefield_Things\\\">Internet of Battlefield Things<\\/span><\\/h4><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The&nbsp;<b>Internet of Battlefield Things<\\/b>&nbsp;(<b>IoT<\\/b>) is a project initiated and executed by the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/United_States_Army_Research_Laboratory\\\" title=\\\"United States Army Research Laboratory\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">U.S. Army Research Laboratory (ARL)<\\/a>&nbsp;that focuses on the basic science related to the IoT that enhance the capabilities of Army soldiers.&nbsp;In 2017, ARL launched the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/IoBT-CRA\\\" title=\\\"IoBT-CRA\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Internet of Battlefield Things Collaborative Research Alliance (IoT-CRA)<\\/a>, establishing a working collaboration between industry, university, and Army researchers to advance the theoretical foundations of IoT technologies and their applications to Army operations.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-98\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/p><h4 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-headline\\\" id=\\\"Ocean_of_Things\\\">Ocean of Things<\\/span><\\/h4><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The&nbsp;<b>Ocean of Things<\\/b>&nbsp;project is a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/DARPA\\\" title=\\\"DARPA\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">DARPA<\\/a>-led program designed to establish an Internet of things across large ocean areas for the purposes of collecting, monitoring, and analyzing environmental and vessel activity data. The project entails the deployment of about 50,000 floats that house a passive sensor suite that autonomously detects and track military and commercial vessels as part of a cloud-based network.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"The Internet of Military Things (IoMT) is the application of IoT technologies in the military domain for the purposes of reconnaissance, surveillance, and other combat-related objectives. It is heavily influenced by the future prospects of warfare in an urban environment and involves the use of sensors, munitions, vehicles, robots, human-wearable biometrics, and other smart technology that is relevant on the battlefield.\"}', '63791644906656.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'iot-military-applications', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `excerpt`, `feature_img_name`, `feature_img_original_name`, `feature_img_mime`, `feature_img_ext`, `status`, `tags`, `read`, `headline`, `front_slider`, `highlight`, `publish_status`, `published_year`, `published_number`, `published_at`, `slug`, `addedby_id`, `writer_id`, `editedby_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(52, '{\"en\":\"History about software\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Beginning in the 1960s, software engineering was seen as its own type of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Engineering\\\" title=\\\"Engineering\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">engineering<\\/a>. Additionally, the development of software engineering was seen as a struggle. It was difficult to keep up with the hardware which caused many problems for software engineers. Problems included software that was over budget, exceeded deadlines, required extensive&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Debugging\\\" title=\\\"Debugging\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">debugging<\\/a>&nbsp;and maintenance, and unsuccessfully met the needs of consumers or was never even completed. In 1968&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/NATO\\\" title=\\\"NATO\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">NATO<\\/a>&nbsp;held the first Software Engineering conference where issues related to software were addressed: guidelines and best practices for the development of software were established.&nbsp;<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">The origins of the term \\\"software engineering\\\" have been attributed to various sources. The term \\\"software engineering\\\" appeared in a list of services offered by companies in the June 1965 issue of&nbsp;<a rel=\\\"nofollow\\\" class=\\\"external text\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.bitsavers.org\\/magazines\\/Computers_And_Automation\\/196506.pdf\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(51, 102, 187); background-image: url(&quot;\\/\\/upload.wikimedia.org\\/wikipedia\\/commons\\/2\\/23\\/Icons-mini-file_acrobat.gif&quot;); background-position: right center; background-size: initial; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; padding-right: 18px;\\\">COMPUTERS and AUTOMATION<\\/a>&nbsp;and was used more formally in the August 1966 issue of Communications of the ACM (Volume 9, number 8) \\u201cletter to the ACM membership\\u201d by the ACM President Anthony A. Oettinger,&nbsp;it is also associated with the title of a NATO conference in 1968 by Professor&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Friedrich_L._Bauer\\\" title=\\\"Friedrich L. Bauer\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Friedrich L. Bauer<\\/a>, the first conference on software engineering.&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Margaret_Hamilton_(software_engineer)\\\" title=\\\"Margaret Hamilton (software engineer)\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Margaret Hamilton<\\/a>&nbsp;described the discipline \\\"software engineering\\\" during the Apollo missions to give what they were doing legitimacy.&nbsp;At the time there was perceived to be a \\\"<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_crisis\\\" title=\\\"Software crisis\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">software crisis<\\/a>\\\".&nbsp;The 40th International Conference on Software Engineering (ICSE 2018) celebrates 50 years of \\\"Software Engineering\\\" with the Plenary Sessions\' keynotes of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Frederick_Brooks\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Frederick Brooks\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Frederick Brooks<\\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Margaret_Hamilton_(scientist)\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Margaret Hamilton (scientist)\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Margaret Hamilton<\\/a>.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In 1984, the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_Engineering_Institute\\\" title=\\\"Software Engineering Institute\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Software Engineering Institute<\\/a>&nbsp;(SEI) was established as a federally funded research and development centre headquartered on the campus of Carnegie Mellon University in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, United States.&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Watts_Humphrey\\\" title=\\\"Watts Humphrey\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Watts Humphrey<\\/a>&nbsp;founded the SEI Software Process Program, aimed at understanding and managing the software engineering process. The Process Maturity Levels introduced would become the Capability Maturity Model Integration for Development(CMMI-DEV), which has defined how the US Government evaluates the abilities of a software development team.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Modern, generally accepted best practices for software engineering have been collected by the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/ISO\\/IEC_JTC_1\\/SC_7\\\" title=\\\"ISO\\/IEC JTC 1\\/SC 7\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">ISO\\/IEC JTC 1\\/SC 7<\\/a>&nbsp;subcommittee and published as the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_Engineering_Body_of_Knowledge\\\" title=\\\"Software Engineering Body of Knowledge\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Software Engineering Body of Knowledge<\\/a>&nbsp;(SWEBOK).&nbsp;Software engineering is considered one of the major&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Computing\\\" title=\\\"Computing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">computing<\\/a>&nbsp;disciplines<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Beginning in the 1960s, software engineering was seen as its own type of engineering. Additionally, the development of software engineering was seen as a struggle. It was difficult to keep up with the hardware which caused many problems for software engineers. Problems included software that was over budget, exceeded deadlines, required extensive debugging and maintenance, and unsuccessfully met the needs of consumers or was never even completed. In 1968 NATO held the first Software Engineering conference where issues related to software were addressed: guidelines and best practices for the development of software were established.\"}', '37991644907116.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 1, 1, 1, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'history-about-software', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(53, '{\"en\":\"Definitions and terminology controversies\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">Notable definitions of software engineering include:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"list-style-image: url(\'..\\/..\\/..\\/w\\/skins\\/Vector\\/resources\\/common\\/images\\/bullet-icon.svg?d4515\'); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">\\\"The systematic application of scientific and technological knowledge, methods, and experience to the design, implementation, testing, and documentation of software\\\"&mdash;The Bureau of Labor Statistics&mdash;<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"IEEE\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/IEEE\\\">IEEE<\\/a>&nbsp;<em>Systems and software engineering &ndash; Vocabulary<\\/em><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-IEEE24765_17-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">\\\"The application of a systematic, disciplined, quantifiable approach to the development, operation, and maintenance of&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Software\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software\\\">software<\\/a>\\\"&mdash;<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"IEEE\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/IEEE\\\">IEEE<\\/a>&nbsp;<em>Standard Glossary of Software Engineering Terminology<\\/em><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-IEEE610a_18-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">\\\"an engineering discipline that is concerned with all aspects of software production\\\"&mdash;<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Ian Sommerville (academic)\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Ian_Sommerville_(academic)\\\">Ian Sommerville<\\/a><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-Sommerville1_19-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">\\\"the establishment and use of sound engineering principles in order to economically obtain software that is reliable and works efficiently on real machines\\\"&mdash;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Friedrich L. Bauer\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Friedrich_L._Bauer\\\">Fritz Bauer<\\/a><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-Bauer1_20-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">\\\"a branch of computer science that deals with the design, implementation, and maintenance of complex&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Computer program\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Computer_program\\\">computer programs<\\/a>\\\"&mdash;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Merriam-Webster\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Merriam-Webster\\\">Merriam-Webster<\\/a><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-21\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">\\\"\'software engineering\' encompasses not just the act of writing code, but all of the tools and processes an organization uses to build and maintain that code over time. [...] Software engineering can be thought of as \'programming integrated over time.\'\\\"&mdash;Software Engineering at Google<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-22\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">The term has also been used less formally:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul style=\\\"list-style-image: url(\'..\\/..\\/..\\/w\\/skins\\/Vector\\/resources\\/common\\/images\\/bullet-icon.svg?d4515\'); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">as the informal contemporary term for the broad range of activities that were formerly called&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Computer programming\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Computer_programming\\\">computer programming<\\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Systems analysis\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Systems_analysis\\\">systems analysis<\\/a>;<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-23\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">as the broad term for all aspects of the&nbsp;<em>practice<\\/em>&nbsp;of computer programming, as opposed to the&nbsp;<em>theory<\\/em>&nbsp;of computer programming, which is formally studied as a sub-discipline of&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Computer science\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Computer_science\\\">computer science<\\/a>;<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-p._26_24-0\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\">as the term embodying the&nbsp;<em>advocacy<\\/em>&nbsp;of a specific approach to computer programming, one that urges that it be treated as an&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Engineering\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Engineering\\\">engineering<\\/a>&nbsp;discipline rather than an art or a craft, and advocates the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Codification (law)\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Codification_(law)\\\">codification<\\/a>&nbsp;of recommended practices.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-25\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><\\/sup><\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span id=\\\"Etymology_of_.22software_engineer.22\\\"><\\/span><span id=\\\"Etymology_of_&quot;software_engineer&quot;\\\" class=\\\"mw-headline\\\">Etymology of \\\"software engineer\\\"<\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Margaret Hamilton (scientist)\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Margaret_Hamilton_(scientist)\\\">Margaret Hamilton<\\/a>&nbsp;promoted the term \\\"software engineering\\\" during her work on the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Apollo program\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Apollo_program\\\">Apollo program<\\/a>. The term \\\"engineering\\\" was used to acknowledge that the work should be taken just as seriously as other contributions toward the advancement of technology. Hamilton details her use of the term:<\\/p>\\r\\n<blockquote style=\\\"overflow: hidden; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 8px 32px; border-left: none; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0px;\\\">When I first came up with the term, no one had heard of it before, at least in our world. It was an ongoing joke for a long time. They liked to kid me about my radical ideas. It was a memorable day when one of the most respected hardware gurus explained to everyone in a meeting that he agreed with me that the process of building software should also be considered an engineering discipline, just like with hardware. Not because of his acceptance of the new \\\"term\\\" per se, but because we had earned his and the acceptance of the others in the room as being in an engineering field in its own right.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-26\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_engineering#cite_note-26\\\">[26]<\\/a><\\/sup><\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/blockquote>\\r\\n<h3 style=\\\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\"><span id=\\\"Suitability_of_the_term\\\" class=\\\"mw-headline\\\">Suitability of the term<\\/span><span class=\\\"mw-editsection\\\" style=\\\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; margin-right: 0px;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-editsection-bracket\\\" style=\\\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: #54595d;\\\">[<\\/span><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none; white-space: nowrap;\\\" title=\\\"Edit section: Suitability of the term\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/w\\/index.php?title=Software_engineering&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\\\">edit<\\/a><span class=\\\"mw-editsection-bracket\\\" style=\\\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: #54595d;\\\">]<\\/span><\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\\\">Individual commentators have disagreed sharply on how to define&nbsp;<em>software engineering<\\/em>&nbsp;or its legitimacy as an engineering discipline.&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"David Parnas\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/David_Parnas\\\">David Parnas<\\/a>&nbsp;has said that software engineering is, in fact, a form of engineering.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-27\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_engineering#cite_note-27\\\">[27]<\\/a><\\/sup><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-28\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_engineering#cite_note-28\\\">[28]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Steve McConnell\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Steve_McConnell\\\">Steve McConnell<\\/a>&nbsp;has said that it is not, but that it should be.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-29\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_engineering#cite_note-29\\\">[29]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Donald Knuth\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Donald_Knuth\\\">Donald Knuth<\\/a>&nbsp;has said that programming is an art and a science.<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-30\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_engineering#cite_note-30\\\">[30]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Edsger W. Dijkstra\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Edsger_W._Dijkstra\\\">Edsger W. Dijkstra<\\/a>&nbsp;claimed that the terms&nbsp;<em>software engineering<\\/em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>software engineer<\\/em>&nbsp;have been misused<sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<em><a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:No original research\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Synthesis_of_published_material\\\"><span title=\\\"The material near this tag may be based upon an improper synthesis of sources. (April 2015)\\\">improper synthesis?<\\/span><\\/a><\\/em>]<\\/sup>&nbsp;and should be considered harmful, particularly in the&nbsp;<a style=\\\"text-decoration-line: none; color: #0645ad; background: none;\\\" title=\\\"United States\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/United_States\\\">United States<\\/a><\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Margaret Hamilton promoted the term \\\"software engineering\\\" during her work on the Apollo program. The term \\\"engineering\\\" was used to acknowledge that the work should be taken just as seriously as other contributions toward the advancement of technology. Hamilton details her use of the term:\"}', '22611644907521.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'definitions-and-terminology-controversies', 1, NULL, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(54, '{\"en\":\"Software design\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_design\\\" title=\\\"Software design\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Software design<\\/a>&nbsp;is about the process of defining the architecture, components, interfaces, and other characteristics of a system or component. This is also called&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_architecture\\\" title=\\\"Software architecture\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">software architecture<\\/a>. Software design is divided into three different levels of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Design\\\" title=\\\"Design\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">design<\\/a>. The three levels are&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Interface_Design\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Interface Design\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">interface design<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_architecture\\\" title=\\\"Software architecture\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">architectural design<\\/a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Detailed_design_document\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Detailed design document\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">detailed design<\\/a>. Interface design is the interaction between a system and its environment. This happens at a high level of abstraction along with the inner workings of the system. Architectural design has to do with the major components of a system and their responsibilities, properties, interfaces, and their relationships and interactions that occur between them. Detailed design is the internal elements of all the major system components, their properties, relationships, processing, and usually their&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Algorithm\\\" title=\\\"Algorithm\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">algorithms<\\/a>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Data_structure\\\" title=\\\"Data structure\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">data structures<\\/a>.<\\/p><h3 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-headline\\\" id=\\\"Software_construction\\\">Software construction<\\/span><\\/h3><div role=\\\"note\\\" class=\\\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\\\" style=\\\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Main article:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_construction\\\" title=\\\"Software construction\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Software construction<\\/a><\\/div><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Software construction, the main activity of software development,&nbsp;is the combination of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Computer_programming\\\" title=\\\"Computer programming\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">programming<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Unit_testing\\\" title=\\\"Unit testing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">unit testing<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Integration_testing\\\" title=\\\"Integration testing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">integration testing<\\/a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Debugging\\\" title=\\\"Debugging\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">debugging<\\/a>. Testing during this phase is generally performed by the programmer while the software is under construction, to verify what was just written and decide when the code is ready to be sent to the next step.<\\/p><h3 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-headline\\\" id=\\\"Software_testing\\\">Software testing<\\/span><\\/h3><div role=\\\"note\\\" class=\\\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\\\" style=\\\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Main article:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_testing\\\" title=\\\"Software testing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Software testing<\\/a><\\/div><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_testing\\\" title=\\\"Software testing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Software testing<\\/a>&nbsp;is an empirical, technical investigation conducted to provide stakeholders with information about the quality of the product or service under test, with different approaches such as&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Unit_testing\\\" title=\\\"Unit testing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">unit testing<\\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Integration_testing\\\" title=\\\"Integration testing\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">integration testing<\\/a>. It is one aspect of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_quality\\\" title=\\\"Software quality\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">software quality<\\/a>. As a separate phase in software development, it is typically performed by&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Quality_assurance\\\" title=\\\"Quality assurance\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">quality assurance<\\/a>&nbsp;staff or a developer other than the one who wrote the code.<\\/p><h3 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span class=\\\"mw-headline\\\" id=\\\"Software_maintenance\\\">Software maintenance<\\/span><\\/h3><div role=\\\"note\\\" class=\\\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\\\" style=\\\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Main article:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_maintenance\\\" title=\\\"Software maintenance\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Software maintenance<\\/a><\\/div><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_maintenance\\\" title=\\\"Software maintenance\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Software maintenance<\\/a>&nbsp;refers to the activities required to provide cost-effective support after shipping the software product. Software maintenance is modifying and updating&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_applications\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Software applications\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">software applications<\\/a>&nbsp;after distribution to correct faults and to improve their performance. The software has a lot to do with the real world and when the real world changes, software maintenance is required. Software maintenance includes&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Error_correction_code\\\" title=\\\"Error correction code\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">error correction<\\/a>, optimization, deletion of unused and discarded features, and enhancement of features that already exist. Usually, maintenance takes up about 40% to 80% of the project cost therefore, focusing on maintenance keeps the costs down.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Software design is about the process of defining the architecture, components, interfaces, and other characteristics of a system or component. This is also called software architecture. Software design is divided into three different levels of design. The three levels are interface design, architectural design, and detailed design. Interface design is the interaction between a system and its environment. This happens at a high level of abstraction along with the inner workings of the system. Architectural design has to do with the major components of a system and their responsibilities, properties, interfaces, and their relationships and interactions that occur between them. Detailed design is the internal elements of all the major system components, their properties, relationships, processing, and usually their algorithms and the data structures.\"}', '72261644907895.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'software-design', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `excerpt`, `feature_img_name`, `feature_img_original_name`, `feature_img_mime`, `feature_img_ext`, `status`, `tags`, `read`, `headline`, `front_slider`, `highlight`, `publish_status`, `published_year`, `published_number`, `published_at`, `slug`, `addedby_id`, `writer_id`, `editedby_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(55, '{\"en\":\"Software engineering degree programs\"}', '{\"en\":\"<h3 style=\\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-top: 0.3em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: bold; font-family: sans-serif;\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">Half of all practitioners today have&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Academic_degree\\\" title=\\\"Academic degree\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">degrees<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;in&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Computer_science\\\" title=\\\"Computer science\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">computer science<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">,&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Information_systems\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Information systems\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">information systems<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">, or&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Information_technology\\\" title=\\\"Information technology\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">information technology<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">.<\\/span><sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-weight: 400; line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span title=\\\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (February 2007)\\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;A small, but growing, a number of practitioners have software engineering degrees. In 1987, the&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Department_of_Computing,_Imperial_College_London\\\" title=\\\"Department of Computing, Imperial College London\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">Department of Computing<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;at&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Imperial_College_London\\\" title=\\\"Imperial College London\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">Imperial College London<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;introduced the first three-year software engineering&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Bachelor%27s_degree\\\" title=\\\"Bachelor\'s degree\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">Bachelor\'s degree<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;in the UK and the world; in the following year, the&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/University_of_Sheffield\\\" title=\\\"University of Sheffield\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">University of Sheffield<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;established a similar program.<\\/span><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;In 1996, the&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Rochester_Institute_of_Technology\\\" title=\\\"Rochester Institute of Technology\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">Rochester Institute of Technology<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;established the first software engineering bachelor\'s degree program in the United States, however, it did not obtain&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/ABET\\\" title=\\\"ABET\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">ABET<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;accreditation until 2003, the same time as&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Rice_University\\\" title=\\\"Rice University\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">Rice University<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">,&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Clarkson_University\\\" title=\\\"Clarkson University\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">Clarkson University<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">,&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Milwaukee_School_of_Engineering\\\" title=\\\"Milwaukee School of Engineering\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">Milwaukee School of Engineering<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;<\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Mississippi_State_University\\\" title=\\\"Mississippi State University\\\" style=\\\"font-size: 14px; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);\\\">Mississippi State University<\\/a><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;obtained theirs.<\\/span><span style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400;\\\">&nbsp;In 1997, PSG College of Technology in Coimbatore, India was the first to start a five-year integrated Master of Science degree in Software Engineering.<\\/span><sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-weight: 400; line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span title=\\\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (May 2012)\\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup><br><\\/h3><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Since then, software engineering undergraduate degrees have been established at many universities. A standard international curriculum for undergraduate software engineering degrees,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/SE2004\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"SE2004\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">SE2004<\\/a>, was defined by a steering committee between 2001 and 2004 with funding from the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Association_for_Computing_Machinery\\\" title=\\\"Association for Computing Machinery\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Association for Computing Machinery<\\/a>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/IEEE_Computer_Society\\\" title=\\\"IEEE Computer Society\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">IEEE Computer Society<\\/a>. As of 2004, in the U.S., about 50 universities offer software engineering degrees, which teach both computer science and engineering principles and practices. The first software engineering&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Master%27s_degree\\\" title=\\\"Master\'s degree\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Master\'s degree<\\/a>&nbsp;was established at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Seattle_University\\\" title=\\\"Seattle University\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Seattle University<\\/a>&nbsp;in 1979. Since then graduate software engineering degrees have been made available from many more universities. Likewise in Canada, the Canadian Engineering Accreditation Board (CEAB) of the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Canadian_Council_of_Professional_Engineers\\\" title=\\\"Canadian Council of Professional Engineers\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Canadian Council of Professional Engineers<\\/a>&nbsp;has recognized several software engineering programs.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">In 1998, the US&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Naval_Postgraduate_School\\\" title=\\\"Naval Postgraduate School\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Naval Postgraduate School<\\/a>&nbsp;(NPS) established the first&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Doctorate\\\" title=\\\"Doctorate\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">doctorate<\\/a>&nbsp;program in Software Engineering in the world.<sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span title=\\\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (June 2007)\\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup>&nbsp;Additionally, many online advanced degrees in Software Engineering have appeared such as the Master of Science in Software Engineering (MSE) degree offered through the Computer Science and Engineering Department at&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/California_State_University,_Fullerton\\\" title=\\\"California State University, Fullerton\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">California State University, Fullerton<\\/a>. Steve McConnell opines that because most universities teach computer science rather than software engineering, there is a shortage of true software engineers.&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/%C3%89cole_de_technologie_sup%C3%A9rieure\\\" title=\\\"\\u00c9cole de technologie sup\\u00e9rieure\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">ETS<\\/a>&nbsp;(\\u00c9cole de Technologie sup\\u00e9rieure) University and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/UQAM\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"UQAM\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">UQAM<\\/a>&nbsp;(Universit\\u00e9 du Qu\\u00e9bec \\u00e0 Montr\\u00e9al) were mandated by IEEE to develop the Software Engineering Body of Knowledge (<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/SWEBOK\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"SWEBOK\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">SWEBOK<\\/a>), which has become an ISO standard describing the body of knowledge covered by a software engineer.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Half of all practitioners today have degrees in computer science, information systems, or information technology.[citation needed] A small, but growing, a number of practitioners have software engineering degrees. In 1987, the Department of Computing at Imperial College London introduced the first three-year software engineering Bachelor\'s degree in the UK and the world; in the following year, the University of Sheffield established a similar program. In 1996, the Rochester Institute of Technology established the first software engineering bachelor\'s degree program in the United States, however, it did not obtain ABET accreditation until 2003, the same time as Rice University, Clarkson University, Milwaukee School of Engineering and Mississippi State University obtained theirs. In 1997, PSG College of Technology in Coimbatore, India was the first to start a five-year integrated Master of Science degree in Software Engineering.[citation n\"}', '94481644908812.png', 'Screenshot 2022-02-01 124633.png', NULL, 'png', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'software-engineering-degree-programs', 1, NULL, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
(56, '{\"en\":\"A software Design and implementation\"}', '{\"en\":\"<p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Design and implementation of software vary depending on the complexity of the software. For instance, the design and creation of&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Microsoft_Word\\\" title=\\\"Microsoft Word\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Microsoft Word<\\/a>&nbsp;took much more time than designing and developing&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Microsoft_Notepad\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Microsoft Notepad\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Microsoft Notepad<\\/a>&nbsp;because the latter has much more basic functionality.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Software is usually developed in&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Integrated_development_environment\\\" title=\\\"Integrated development environment\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">integrated development environments<\\/a>&nbsp;(IDE) like&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Eclipse_(software)\\\" title=\\\"Eclipse (software)\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Eclipse<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/IntelliJ_IDEA\\\" title=\\\"IntelliJ IDEA\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">IntelliJ<\\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Microsoft_Visual_Studio\\\" title=\\\"Microsoft Visual Studio\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Microsoft Visual Studio<\\/a>&nbsp;that can simplify the process and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Compiler\\\" title=\\\"Compiler\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">compile<\\/a>&nbsp;the software.<sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span title=\\\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2021)\\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup>&nbsp;As noted in a different section, the software is usually created on top of existing software and the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Application_programming_interface\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Application programming interface\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">application programming interface<\\/a>&nbsp;(API) that the underlying software provides like&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/GTK%2B\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"GTK+\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">GTK+<\\/a>, JavaBeans or&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Swing_(Java)\\\" title=\\\"Swing (Java)\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Swing<\\/a>.<sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span title=\\\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2021)\\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup>&nbsp;Libraries (APIs) can be categorized by their purpose. For instance, the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Spring_Framework\\\" title=\\\"Spring Framework\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Spring Framework<\\/a>&nbsp;is used for implementing&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Enterprise_application\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Enterprise application\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">enterprise applications<\\/a>, the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Windows_Forms\\\" title=\\\"Windows Forms\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Windows Forms<\\/a>&nbsp;library is used for designing graphical user interface (GUI) applications like Microsoft Word, and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Windows_Communication_Foundation\\\" title=\\\"Windows Communication Foundation\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Windows Communication Foundation<\\/a>&nbsp;is used for designing&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Web_service\\\" title=\\\"Web service\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">web services<\\/a>.<sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span title=\\\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2021)\\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup>&nbsp;When a program is designed, it relies upon the API. For instance, a Microsoft Windows desktop application might call API functions in the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/.NET_Framework\\\" title=\\\".NET Framework\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">.NET<\\/a>&nbsp;Windows Forms library like&nbsp;<i>Form1.Close()<\\/i>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<i>Form1.Show()<\\/i>&nbsp;to close or open the application. Without these APIs, the programmer needs to write these functionalities entirely themselves. Companies like&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Oracle_Corporation\\\" title=\\\"Oracle Corporation\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Oracle<\\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Microsoft\\\" title=\\\"Microsoft\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Microsoft<\\/a>&nbsp;provide their own APIs so that many applications are written using the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Library_(computing)\\\" title=\\\"Library (computing)\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">software libraries<\\/a>&nbsp;that usually have numerous APIs in them.<sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span title=\\\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2021)\\\">citation needed<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Data_structure\\\" title=\\\"Data structure\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">Data structures<\\/a>&nbsp;such as&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Hash_table\\\" title=\\\"Hash table\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">hash tables<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Array_data_type\\\" title=\\\"Array data type\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">arrays<\\/a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Binary_tree\\\" title=\\\"Binary tree\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">binary trees<\\/a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Algorithm\\\" title=\\\"Algorithm\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">algorithms<\\/a>&nbsp;such as&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Quicksort\\\" title=\\\"Quicksort\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">quicksort<\\/a>, can be useful for creating software.<\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">Computer software has special economic characteristics that make its design, creation, and distribution different from most other economic goods.<sup class=\\\"noprint Inline-Template\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\\\">[<i><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Wikipedia:Citing_sources\\\" title=\\\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span title=\\\"Statement needs to be more specific about the content to which it refers. (May 2012)\\\">specify<\\/span><\\/a><\\/i>]<\\/sup><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-22\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software#cite_note-22\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">[22]<\\/a><\\/sup><sup id=\\\"cite_ref-23\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software#cite_note-23\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">[23]<\\/a><\\/sup><\\/p><p style=\\\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\\\">A person who creates software is called a&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Programmer\\\" title=\\\"Programmer\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">programmer<\\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Software_engineer\\\" class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Software engineer\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">software engineer<\\/a>&nbsp;or software developer, terms that all have a similar meaning. More informal terms for programmer also exist such as \\\"coder\\\" and \\\"hacker\\\"&nbsp;\\u2013 although the use of the latter word may cause confusion because it is more often used to mean&nbsp;<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Security_hacker\\\" title=\\\"Security hacker\\\" style=\\\"color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\">someone who illegally breaks into computer systems<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"}', '{\"en\":\"Design and implementation of software vary depending on the complexity of the software. For instance, the design and creation of Microsoft Word took much more time than designing and developing Microsoft Notepad because the latter has much more basic functionality.\"}', '66211644909019.jpg', '248892865_1341328823003887_2371429631831995283_n.jpg', NULL, 'jpg', NULL, '{\"en\":null}', 0, 0, 1, 0, 'published', 0, 0, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', 'a-software-design-and-implementation', 1, 1, NULL, '2026-01-13 15:15:46', '2026-01-13 15:15:46'),
